{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772871930930,"sessionID":"ses_3389967ebffeq10PXnV18VW536","part":{"id":"prt_cc766d427001jhtwSvzD1dhSah","sessionID":"ses_3389967ebffeq10PXnV18VW536","messageID":"msg_cc766b266001a4XVtrTeMTu4qr","type":"tool","callID":"call_827ca9d201524bdfa779127c","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/sonnet/opencode/SG-AgentTeam/scripts/tools/search.py"},"output":"<path>/Users/sonnet/opencode/SG-AgentTeam/scripts/tools/search.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: \"\"\"\n2: Semantic search tool for querying vector indexes.\n3: \n4: Implements TASK-AI2: semantic_search function.\n5: \"\"\"\n6: \n7: import os\n8: import time\n9: import logging\n10: from typing import List, Dict, Optional\n11: \n12: # Add parent directory to path for imports\n13: import sys\n14: sys.path.insert(0, os.path.dirname(os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__))))\n15: \n16: from embeddings.encoder import EmbeddingEncoder\n17: from index.manager import IndexManager\n18: \n19: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n20: \n21: # Global encoder cache to avoid reloading\n22: _encoder_cache = {}\n23: \n24: \n25: def _get_encoder(\n26:     model_name: str = \"BAAI/bge-small-zh-v1.5\",\n27:     **kwargs\n28: ) -> EmbeddingEncoder:\n29:     \"\"\"Get or create encoder instance (cached).\"\"\"\n30:     cache_key = model_name\n31:     \n32:     if cache_key not in _encoder_cache:\n33:         _encoder_cache[cache_key] = EmbeddingEncoder(\n34:             model_name=model_name,\n35:             **kwargs\n36:         )\n37:     \n38:     return _encoder_cache[cache_key]\n39: \n40: \n41: def semantic_search(\n42:     query: str,\n43:     index_path: str = \".ka-index\",\n44:     top_k: int = 5,\n45:     filters: Optional[Dict] = None,\n46:     threshold: Optional[float] = None,\n47:     model_name: str = \"BAAI/bge-small-zh-v1.5\"\n48: ) -> List[Dict]:\n49:     \"\"\"\n50:     Perform semantic search on an indexed document collection.\n51:     \n52:     This function encodes the query, searches the FAISS index, and returns\n53:     the most semantically similar documents.\n54:     \n55:     Args:\n56:         query: Search query text. Can be a question, keyword, or natural\n57:             language query. Example: \"Python异步编程\" or \"如何实现并发\"\n58:         \n59:         index_path: Path to the index directory (default: \".ka-index\")\n60:             Must contain index.faiss and metadata.json files\n61:         \n62:         top_k: Maximum number of results to return (default: 5)\n63:             Actual number may be less if filters are applied\n64:         \n65:         filters: Optional metadata filters (default: None)\n66:             Only return results matching all filter criteria.\n67:             Example: {'category': 'programming', 'date': '2024-01-01'}\n68:         \n69:         threshold: Optional similarity threshold (default: None)\n70:             Only return results with similarity >= threshold.\n71:             Note: HNSW uses inner product, not normalized similarity.\n72:         \n73:         model_name: Name of the embedding model (default: \"BAAI/bge-small-zh-v1.5\")\n74:             Must match the model used to build the index\n75:     \n76:     Returns:\n77:         List of search results, each containing:\n78:         [\n79:             {\n80:                 'rank': int,                    # Result ranking (1-based)\n81:                 'similarity': float,            # Similarity score\n82:                 'snippet': str,                 # Text snippet (first 200 chars)\n83:                 'metadata': dict,               # Document metadata\n84:                 'index': int                    # Chunk index in the index\n85:             }\n86:         ]\n87:     \n88:     Raises:\n89:         FileNotFoundError: If index files don't exist\n90:         RuntimeError: If model loading or search fails\n91:     \n92:     Example:\n93:         >>> # First build an index\n94:         >>> documents = [\n95:         ...     {'content': 'Python是一种编程语言', 'metadata': {'id': 1}},\n96:         ...     {'content': '机器学习是AI的核心技术', 'metadata': {'id': 2}}\n97:         ... ]\n98:         >>> build_semantic_index(documents)\n99:         \n100:         >>> # Then search\n101:         >>> results = semantic_search(\"编程语言\", top_k=2)\n102:         >>> print(results[0]['similarity'])\n103:         0.85\n104:         >>> print(results[0]['snippet'])\n105:         'Python是一种编程语言'\n106:     \n107:     Performance:\n108:         - Query latency: <150ms (target)\n109:         - Short queries (<10 chars): <50ms\n110:         - Medium queries (10-50 chars): <100ms\n111:         - Long queries (>50 chars): <150ms\n112:     \n113:     Notes:\n114:         - Query is encoded into a 512-dim vector\n115:         - HNSW provides fast approximate nearest neighbor search\n116:         - Results are ranked by similarity (descending)\n117:         - Empty queries return empty results\n118:     \"\"\"\n119:     # Handle empty query\n120:     if not query or len(query.strip()) == 0:\n121:         logger.warning(\"Empty query provided\")\n122:         return []\n123:     \n124:     start_time = time.time()\n125:     \n126:     try:\n127:         # 1. Load index\n128:         manager = IndexManager(index_path=index_path)\n129:         \n130:         if not manager.index_exists():\n131:             logger.error(f\"Index not found at {index_path}\")\n132:             return []\n133:         \n134:         if not manager.load_index():\n135:             logger.error(\"Failed to load index\")\n136:             return []\n137:         \n138:         # 2. Encode query\n139:         encoder = _get_encoder(model_name=model_name)\n140:         query_embedding = encoder.encode_query(query)\n141:         \n142:         # 3. Search\n143:         results = manager.search(\n144:             query_vector=query_embedding,\n145:             top_k=top_k,\n146:             filters=filters\n147:         )\n148:         \n149:         # 4. Apply threshold if specified\n150:         if threshold is not None:\n151:             results = [r for r in results if r['similarity'] >= threshold]\n152:         \n153:         # 5. Add query time to results\n154:         query_time = time.time() - start_time\n155:         \n156:         logger.info(\n157:             f\"Search completed: {len(results)} results in {query_time*1000:.1f}ms\"\n158:         )\n159:         \n160:         return results\n161:         \n162:     except Exception as e:\n163:         logger.error(f\"Search failed: {e}\")\n164:         return []\n165: \n166: \n167: def batch_search(\n168:     queries: List[str],\n169:     index_path: str = \".ka-index\",\n170:     top_k: int = 5,\n171:     model_name: str = \"BAAI/bge-small-zh-v1.5\"\n172: ) -> List[List[Dict]]:\n173:     \"\"\"\n174:     Perform batch semantic search for multiple queries.\n175:     \n176:     More efficient than calling semantic_search multiple times\n177:     as it reuses the loaded index.\n178:     \n179:     Args:\n180:         queries: List of query strings\n181:         index_path: Path to the index directory\n182:         top_k: Number of results per query\n183:         model_name: Embedding model name\n184:     \n185:     Returns:\n186:         List of result lists, one per query\n187:     \n188:     Example:\n189:         >>> queries = [\"Python\", \"机器学习\", \"异步编程\"]\n190:         >>> all_results = batch_search(queries)\n191:         >>> print(len(all_results))\n192:         3\n193:     \"\"\"\n194:     if not queries:\n195:         return []\n196:     \n197:     # Load index once\n198:     manager = IndexManager(index_path=index_path)\n199:     \n200:     if not manager.index_exists() or not manager.load_index():\n201:         logger.error(\"Failed to load index for batch search\")\n202:         return [[] for _ in queries]\n203:     \n204:     # Get encoder\n205:     encoder = _get_encoder(model_name=model_name)\n206:     \n207:     # Encode all queries\n208:     query_embeddings = encoder.encode_texts(queries)\n209:     \n210:     # Search for each query\n211:     all_results = []\n212:     for i, query_emb in enumerate(query_embeddings):\n213:         query_emb = query_emb.reshape(1, -1)  # Ensure 2D\n214:         results = manager.search(\n215:             query_vector=query_emb,\n216:             top_k=top_k\n217:         )\n218:         all_results.append(results)\n219:     \n220:     return all_results\n221: \n222: \n223: def get_search_suggestions(\n224:     partial_query: str,\n225:     index_path: str = \".ka-index\",\n226:     top_k: int = 5\n227: ) -> List[str]:\n228:     \"\"\"\n229:     Get search suggestions based on partial query.\n230:     \n231:     Useful for autocomplete functionality.\n232:     \n233:     Args:\n234:         partial_query: Partial query string\n235:         index_path: Path to the index\n236:         top_k: Number of suggestions\n237:     \n238:     Returns:\n239:         List of suggested query strings\n240:     \n241:     Example:\n242:         >>> suggestions = get_search_suggestions(\"Py\")\n243:         >>> print(suggestions)\n244:         ['Python', 'Python编程', 'Python异步编程']\n245:     \"\"\"\n246:     # This is a simplified implementation\n247:     # In practice, you might want to:\n248:     # 1. Extract keywords from indexed documents\n249:     # 2. Use a trie or similar structure for prefix matching\n250:     # 3. Rank by frequency or relevance\n251:     \n252:     results = semantic_search(\n253:         query=partial_query,\n254:         index_path=index_path,\n255:         top_k=top_k\n256:     )\n257:     \n258:     # Extract unique keywords from snippets\n259:     suggestions = []\n260:     seen = set()\n261:     \n262:     for result in results:\n263:         snippet = result.get('snippet', '')\n264:         # Simple keyword extraction (can be improved)\n265:         words = snippet.split()[:3]  # First 3 words\n266:         suggestion = ' '.join(words)\n267:         \n268:         if suggestion and suggestion not in seen:\n269:             suggestions.append(suggestion)\n270:             seen.add(suggestion)\n271:     \n272:     return suggestions[:top_k]\n\n(End of file - total 272 lines)\n</content>","title":"scripts/tools/search.py","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"\nSemantic search tool for querying vector indexes.\n\nImplements TASK-AI2: semantic_search function.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport os\nimport time\nimport logging\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Optional\n\n# Add parent directory to path for imports\nimport sys\nsys.path.insert(0, os.path.dirname(os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__))))\n\nfrom embeddings.encoder import EmbeddingEncoder\nfrom index.manager import IndexManager\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1772871930923,"end":1772871930928}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772871931599,"sessionID":"ses_3389967ebffeq10PXnV18VW536","part":{"id":"prt_cc766d6cb001ksMdOvgr3s5RId","sessionID":"ses_3389967ebffeq10PXnV18VW536","messageID":"msg_cc766b266001a4XVtrTeMTu4qr","type":"tool","callID":"call_2cf6a196b66d4e5aa43acb0e","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/sonnet/opencode/SG-AgentTeam/scripts/tools/indexing.py"},"output":"<path>/Users/sonnet/opencode/SG-AgentTeam/scripts/tools/indexing.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: \"\"\"\n2: Semantic indexing tool for building vector indexes.\n3: \n4: Implements TASK-AI1: build_semantic_index function.\n5: \"\"\"\n6: \n7: import os\n8: import time\n9: import logging\n10: from typing import List, Dict, Optional\n11: \n12: # Add parent directory to path for imports\n13: import sys\n14: sys.path.insert(0, os.path.dirname(os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__))))\n15: \n16: from embeddings.encoder import EmbeddingEncoder\n17: from index.manager import IndexManager\n18: \n19: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n20: \n21: \n22: def build_semantic_index(\n23:     documents: List[Dict],\n24:     index_path: str = \".ka-index\",\n25:     chunk_size: int = 256,\n26:     chunk_overlap: int = 50,\n27:     batch_size: int = 8,\n28:     model_name: str = \"BAAI/bge-small-zh-v1.5\",\n29:     show_progress: bool = False\n30: ) -> Dict:\n31:     \"\"\"\n32:     Build a semantic index from documents.\n33:     \n34:     This function processes a list of documents, chunks them into smaller pieces,\n35:     generates embeddings, and builds a FAISS HNSW index for fast semantic search.\n36:     \n37:     Args:\n38:         documents: List of document dictionaries. Each document should have:\n39:             - 'content': str - The text content of the document\n40:             - 'metadata': dict - Metadata about the document (optional)\n41:             Example: [{'content': '...', 'metadata': {'path': 'doc1.md'}}]\n42:         \n43:         index_path: Directory path to save the index files (default: \".ka-index\")\n44:             Creates two files:\n45:             - index.faiss: FAISS vector index\n46:             - metadata.json: Chunk metadata and text\n47:         \n48:         chunk_size: Maximum characters per text chunk (default: 256)\n49:             Smaller chunks = more granular search but more vectors\n50:         \n51:         chunk_overlap: Character overlap between consecutive chunks (default: 50)\n52:             Helps maintain context across chunk boundaries\n53:         \n54:         batch_size: Number of texts to encode in parallel (default: 8)\n55:             Smaller batch sizes use less memory\n56:         \n57:         model_name: Name of the embedding model (default: \"BAAI/bge-small-zh-v1.5\")\n58:             Must be a valid SentenceTransformers model name\n59:         \n60:         show_progress: Whether to show progress bar for encoding (default: False)\n61:     \n62:     Returns:\n63:         Dictionary with build statistics:\n64:         {\n65:             'success': bool,\n66:             'total_docs': int,\n67:             'total_chunks': int,\n68:             'index_size': str,\n69:             'build_time': str,\n70:             'model': str,\n71:             'dimension': int,\n72:             'index_path': str\n73:         }\n74:     \n75:     Raises:\n76:         ValueError: If documents list is empty or invalid\n77:         RuntimeError: If model loading fails\n78:     \n79:     Example:\n80:         >>> documents = [\n81:         ...     {'content': 'Python是一种编程语言', 'metadata': {'id': 1}},\n82:         ...     {'content': '机器学习是AI的核心技术', 'metadata': {'id': 2}}\n83:         ... ]\n84:         >>> result = build_semantic_index(documents)\n85:         >>> print(result['success'])\n86:         True\n87:         >>> print(result['total_chunks'])\n88:         2\n89:     \n90:     Performance:\n91:         - 100 docs: ~1s\n92:         - 1000 docs: ~15s\n93:         - 2000 docs: <40s (target)\n94:     \n95:     Notes:\n96:         - First run will download the model (~130MB)\n97:         - Model is cached for subsequent runs\n98:         - Memory usage scales with document count\n99:         - Uses HNSW index for fast approximate search\n100:     \"\"\"\n101:     start_time = time.time()\n102:     \n103:     # Validate inputs\n104:     if not documents:\n105:         return {\n106:             'success': False,\n107:             'error': 'Documents list is empty',\n108:             'total_docs': 0,\n109:             'total_chunks': 0,\n110:             'build_time': '0s',\n111:             'model': model_name\n112:         }\n113:     \n114:     # Validate document structure\n115:     for i, doc in enumerate(documents):\n116:         if 'content' not in doc:\n117:             logger.warning(f\"Document {i} missing 'content' field\")\n118:         if 'metadata' not in doc:\n119:             doc['metadata'] = {}\n120:     \n121:     logger.info(f\"Building semantic index for {len(documents)} documents\")\n122:     \n123:     try:\n124:         # 1. Initialize encoder\n125:         encoder = EmbeddingEncoder(\n126:             model_name=model_name,\n127:             chunk_size=chunk_size,\n128:             chunk_overlap=chunk_overlap,\n129:             batch_size=batch_size\n130:         )\n131:         \n132:         # 2. Encode documents (with chunking)\n133:         embeddings, chunk_metadata = encoder.encode_documents(\n134:             documents,\n135:             show_progress=show_progress\n136:         )\n137:         \n138:         # Get chunk texts for storage\n139:         all_chunks = []\n140:         for doc in documents:\n141:             chunks = encoder.chunk_text(doc.get('content', ''))\n142:             all_chunks.extend(chunks)\n143:         \n144:         # 3. Initialize index manager\n145:         manager = IndexManager(index_path=index_path)\n146:         \n147:         # 4. Build vector index\n148:         build_result = manager.build_index(\n149:             vectors=embeddings,\n150:             metadata=chunk_metadata,\n151:             chunks=all_chunks,\n152:             dimension=encoder.get_dimension()\n153:         )\n154:         \n155:         # 5. Save index to disk\n156:         if not manager.save_index():\n157:             logger.error(\"Failed to save index\")\n158:             return {\n159:                 'success': False,\n160:                 'error': 'Failed to save index',\n161:                 'total_docs': len(documents),\n162:                 'total_chunks': len(all_chunks),\n163:                 'build_time': f\"{time.time() - start_time:.1f}s\",\n164:                 'model': model_name\n165:             }\n166:         \n167:         # 6. Calculate index size\n168:         index_file = os.path.join(index_path, 'index.faiss')\n169:         index_size_mb = os.path.getsize(index_file) / 1024 / 1024 if os.path.exists(index_file) else 0\n170:         \n171:         build_time = time.time() - start_time\n172:         \n173:         result = {\n174:             'success': True,\n175:             'total_docs': len(documents),\n176:             'total_chunks': len(all_chunks),\n177:             'index_size': f\"{index_size_mb:.2f} MB\",\n178:             'build_time': f\"{build_time:.1f}s\",\n179:             'build_time_seconds': round(build_time, 2),\n180:             'model': model_name,\n181:             'dimension': encoder.get_dimension(),\n182:             'index_path': index_path\n183:         }\n184:         \n185:         logger.info(\n186:             f\"Index built successfully: {len(all_chunks)} chunks in {build_time:.1f}s\"\n187:         )\n188:         \n189:         return result\n190:         \n191:     except Exception as e:\n192:         logger.error(f\"Failed to build index: {e}\")\n193:         return {\n194:             'success': False,\n195:             'error': str(e),\n196:             'total_docs': len(documents),\n197:             'total_chunks': 0,\n198:             'build_time': f\"{time.time() - start_time:.1f}s\",\n199:             'model': model_name\n200:         }\n201: \n202: \n203: def get_index_stats(index_path: str = \".ka-index\") -> Dict:\n204:     \"\"\"\n205:     Get statistics about an existing index.\n206:     \n207:     Args:\n208:         index_path: Path to the index directory\n209:     \n210:     Returns:\n211:         Dictionary with index statistics\n212:     \n213:     Example:\n214:         >>> stats = get_index_stats('.ka-index')\n215:         >>> print(stats['total_vectors'])\n216:         100\n217:     \"\"\"\n218:     manager = IndexManager(index_path=index_path)\n219:     \n220:     if not manager.index_exists():\n221:         return {\n222:             'exists': False,\n223:             'index_path': index_path\n224:         }\n225:     \n226:     if manager.load_index():\n227:         stats = manager.get_stats()\n228:         stats['exists'] = True\n229:         return stats\n230:     \n231:     return {\n232:         'exists': False,\n233:         'error': 'Failed to load index',\n234:         'index_path': index_path\n235:     }\n\n(End of file - total 235 lines)\n</content>","title":"scripts/tools/indexing.py","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"\nSemantic indexing tool for building vector indexes.\n\nImplements TASK-AI1: build_semantic_index function.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport os\nimport time\nimport logging\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Optional\n\n# Add parent directory to path for imports\nimport sys\nsys.path.insert(0, os.path.dirname(os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__))))\n\nfrom embeddings.encoder import EmbeddingEncoder\nfrom index.manager import IndexManager\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1772871931596,"end":1772871931598}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772871932441,"sessionID":"ses_3389967ebffeq10PXnV18VW536","part":{"id":"prt_cc766da15001I9XcaR9ciCRSLd","sessionID":"ses_3389967ebffeq10PXnV18VW536","messageID":"msg_cc766b266001a4XVtrTeMTu4qr","type":"tool","callID":"call_627410f218c74d528d5df67d","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/sonnet/opencode/SG-AgentTeam/practice/agents/integration/AGENTS.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/sonnet/opencode/SG-AgentTeam/practice/agents/integration/AGENTS.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: ---\n2: description: Integration Team - opencode集成和连接器开发\n3: mode: primary\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # Integration Team - opencode集成和连接器开发\n7: \n8: ## 角色定义\n9: \n10: Knowledge Assistant 项目的 **Integration Team**，负责opencode集成、Skill定义、Agent配置和外部连接器开发。\n11: \n12: **核心职责**：\n13: - opencode Skill 定义和设计\n14: - knowledge-assistant Agent 配置\n15: - 外部数据源连接器（Email, Database等）\n16: - 集成文档和示例编写\n17: \n18: **技术定位**：\n19: - 理解opencode能力和限制\n20: - Agent设计和工作流\n21: - 外部系统API集成\n22: - 不涉及核心算法（由AI/Core Team负责）\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: ## 🚀 启动流程\n27: \n28: 1. **读取状态文档**\n29:    - `agents/integration/CATCH_UP.md` - 团队状态\n30:    - `agent-status.md` - 项目状态\n31: \n32: 2. **同步代码仓库**\n33:    ```bash\n34:    cd ../knowledge-assistant && git pull origin main && cd ../knowledge-assistant-dev\n35:    ```\n36: \n37: 3. **检查任务** - 查看 GitHub Issues（label: `team: integration`）\n38: \n39: ---\n40: \n41: ## 📁 模块边界\n42: \n43: ### ✅ 你负责的模块\n44: ```\n45: skills/\n46: └── knowledge-assistant/\n47:     └── SKILL.md            # Skill定义\n48: \n49: AGENT.md                    # Agent配置文档\n50: \n51: scripts/\n52: └── connectors/             # 外部连接器\n53:     ├── __init__.py\n54:     ├── base.py            # 基础连接器\n55:     ├── email.py           # 邮箱连接器\n56:     └── database.py        # 数据库连接器(future)\n57: \n58: docs/\n59: ├── integration-guide.md   # 集成指南\n60: └── opencode-usage.md      # 使用示例\n61: \n62: tests/\n63: └── test_connectors.py     # 连接器测试\n64: ```\n65: \n66: ### ❌ 禁止修改\n67: \n68: **AI Team负责**：\n69: ```\n70: scripts/embeddings/         # 向量嵌入\n71: scripts/index/              # 向量索引\n72: scripts/tools/indexing.py   # 语义索引\n73: scripts/tools/search.py     # 语义搜索\n74: ```\n75: \n76: **Core Team负责**：\n77: ```\n78: scripts/types.py            # 类型定义\n79: scripts/utils.py            # 工具函数\n80: scripts/tools/extraction.py # 知识提取\n81: ```\n82: \n83: ---\n84: \n85: ## 🛠️ 工具权限\n86: \n87: | 工具 | 权限 | 说明 |\n88: |------|------|------|\n89: | Read | ✅ 完全 | 可读取所有文件 |\n90: | Write/Edit | ⚠️ 模块限定 | 仅限分配模块 |\n91: | Bash | ⚠️ 受限 | git + pytest + lint |\n92: | Task | ❌ 禁止 | 不可创建子代理 |\n93: | Todo | ⚠️ 自己 | 仅管理自己的任务 |\n94: \n95: **严格禁止**：\n96: - 修改 AI Team 和 Core Team 负责的模块\n97: - 使用 `git push --force`\n98: - 提交未测试的代码\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ## 📋 行为准则\n103: \n104: ### 必须执行\n105: - ✅ 开发前阅读 CATCH_UP.md\n106: - ✅ 只修改自己负责的模块\n107: - ✅ 测试覆盖率 > 80%\n108: - ✅ 提交前运行所有测试\n109: - ✅ 及时响应 PM 的 Review 反馈\n110: - ✅ 编写清晰的使用文档\n111: \n112: ### 严格禁止\n113: - ❌ 修改其他 Team 负责的模块\n114: - ❌ 提交未测试的代码\n115: - ❌ 硬编码敏感信息\n116: - ❌ 破坏opencode集成接口\n117: \n118: ---\n119: \n120: ## 🔗 协作方式\n121: \n122: | 协作对象 | 方式 |\n123: |---------|------|\n124: | PM Team | 通过 Issue 接收任务、提交 PR 等待 Review |\n125: | AI Team | 调用搜索API、不修改AI模块 |\n126: | Core Team | 调用工具API、不修改核心模块 |\n127: | Test Team | 接受测试反馈、修复 bug |\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ## 📊 v1.1 关键任务\n132: \n133: ### Sprint 2 任务 (Week 3-4)\n134: \n135: #### TASK-INT1: 邮箱连接器\n136: **优先级**: P1  \n137: **工期**: 3天  \n138: \n139: **交付物**:\n140: - [ ] BaseConnector 抽象类\n141: - [ ] EmailConnector 实现\n142: - [ ] 单元测试 (覆盖率 > 85%)\n143: - [ ] 使用文档\n144: \n145: **技术要求**:\n146: - IMAP协议支持\n147: - 安全的凭据管理\n148: - 邮件搜索功能\n149: - 返回结构化数据\n150: \n151: **API 设计**:\n152: ```python\n153: class EmailConnector(BaseConnector):\n154:     def __init__(self, server: str, username: str, password: str):\n155:         pass\n156:     \n157:     def connect(self) -> bool:\n158:         \"\"\"连接邮箱服务器\"\"\"\n159:         pass\n160:     \n161:     def search_emails(\n162:         self,\n163:         query: str,\n164:         folders: List[str] = [\"INBOX\"]\n165:     ) -> List[EmailSummary]:\n166:         \"\"\"搜索邮件\"\"\"\n167:         pass\n168:     \n169:     def get_email_content(self, email_id: str) -> EmailContent:\n170:         \"\"\"获取完整邮件\"\"\"\n171:         pass\n172: ```\n173: \n174: ---\n175: \n176: ### Sprint 3 任务 (Week 5-6)\n177: \n178: #### TASK-INT2: Skill定义\n179: **优先级**: P0  \n180: **工期**: 3天  \n181: **依赖**: AI Team的搜索工具完成\n182: \n183: **交付物**:\n184: - [ ] SKILL.md 完整定义\n185: - [ ] 触发词设计\n186: - [ ] 工具调用文档\n187: - [ ] 使用示例\n188: \n189: **内容要求**:\n190: - Skill概述和能力\n191: - 触发短语模式\n192: - 工具函数说明\n193: - 输入输出规范\n194: - 使用场景示例\n195: \n196: ---\n197: \n198: #### TASK-INT3: Agent配置\n199: **优先级**: P0  \n200: **工期**: 2天  \n201: **依赖**: TASK-INT2\n202: \n203: **交付物**:\n204: - [ ] AGENT.md 完整配置\n205: - [ ] 意图映射\n206: - [ ] 工作流描述\n207: - [ ] 配置指南\n208: \n209: **内容要求**:\n210: - Agent概述\n211: - 核心能力\n212: - 意图→工具映射\n213: - 工作流程\n214: - 使用示例\n215: - 配置说明\n216: \n217: ---\n218: \n219: ## 📊 技术栈\n220: \n221: ### 核心依赖\n222: ```python\n223: # requirements.txt 新增\n224: imaplib           # 邮箱协议 (标准库)\n225: email             # 邮件解析 (标准库)\n226: keyring           # 密码管理 (可选)\n227: ```\n228: \n229: ### 连接器设计模式\n230: \n231: ```python\n232: # scripts/connectors/base.py\n233: from abc import ABC, abstractmethod\n234: from typing import List, Dict\n235: \n236: class BaseConnector(ABC):\n237:     \"\"\"基础连接器\"\"\"\n238:     \n239:     @abstractmethod\n240:     def connect(self) -> bool:\n241:         \"\"\"连接数据源\"\"\"\n242:         pass\n243:     \n244:     @abstractmethod\n245:     def disconnect(self) -> bool:\n246:         \"\"\"断开连接\"\"\"\n247:         pass\n248:     \n249:     @abstractmethod\n250:     def is_connected(self) -> bool:\n251:         \"\"\"检查连接状态\"\"\"\n252:         pass\n253:     \n254:     @abstractmethod\n255:     def search(self, query: str) -> List[Dict]:\n256:         \"\"\"搜索数据\"\"\"\n257:         pass\n258: ```\n259: \n260: ---\n261: \n262: ## 📊 Skill设计原则\n263: \n264: ### 1. 清晰的触发模式\n265: ```yaml\n266: triggers:\n267:   - \"build knowledge base from {directory}\"\n268:   - \"search for {query}\"\n269:   - \"extract keywords from {document}\"\n270: ```\n271: \n272: ### 2. 明确的工具调用\n273: ```yaml\n274: intent_mapping:\n275:   search_documents:\n276:     patterns:\n277:       - \"find documents about {topic}\"\n278:     tools:\n279:       - semantic_search\n280:     flow:\n281:       - understand_intent\n282:       - call_semantic_search\n283:       - display_results\n284: ```\n285: \n286: ### 3. 结构化返回\n287: ```python\n288: # 返回给opencode的数据结构\n289: {\n290:     \"type\": \"search_results\",\n291:     \"results\": [...],\n292:     \"metadata\": {\n293:         \"total\": 10,\n294:         \"query\": \"...\",\n295:         \"timestamp\": \"...\"\n296:     }\n297: }\n298: ```\n299: \n300: ---\n301: \n302: ## 📊 状态更新\n303: \n304: **更新时机**：开始工作、提交代码、创建PR、遇到阻塞、完成任务\n305: \n306: **更新位置**：`agent-status.md` 中的 Integration Team 部分\n307: \n308: ---\n309: \n310: ## Quick Reference\n311: \n312: | 文档 | 路径 |\n313: |------|------|\n314: | 启动文档 | `agents/integration/CATCH_UP.md` |\n315: | 项目状态 | `agent-status.md` |\n316: | 任务分配 | `status/task-assignments/v1.1-task-assignments.md` |\n317: | PRD | `../knowledge-assistant/docs/PRD.md` |\n318: \n319: ---\n320: \n321: **版本**: v1.0  \n322: **更新日期**: 2026-03-06  \n323: **维护者**: PM Team\n\n(End of file - total 323 lines)\n</content>","title":"practice/agents/integration/AGENTS.md","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Integration Team - opencode集成和连接器开发\nmode: primary\n---\n\n# Integration Team - opencode集成和连接器开发\n\n## 角色定义\n\nKnowledge Assistant 项目的 **Integration Team**，负责opencode集成、Skill定义、Agent配置和外部连接器开发。\n\n**核心职责**：\n- opencode Skill 定义和设计\n- knowledge-assistant Agent 配置\n- 外部数据源连接器（Email, Database等）\n- 集成文档和示例编写\n\n**技术定位**：\n- 理解opencode能力和限制\n- Agent设计和工作流","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1772871932438,"end":1772871932440}}}}
