{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772871940106,"sessionID":"ses_3389967ebffeq10PXnV18VW536","part":{"id":"prt_cc766f801001RaBzVcGHhs14Bp","sessionID":"ses_3389967ebffeq10PXnV18VW536","messageID":"msg_cc766dbfc001kuS2zx2X5TvzeS","type":"tool","callID":"call_fc4da7a8d3954e419b6a27a6","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/sonnet/opencode/SG-AgentTeam/scripts/connectors/email.py"},"output":"<path>/Users/sonnet/opencode/SG-AgentTeam/scripts/connectors/email.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: \"\"\"\n2: Email connector implementation using IMAP protocol.\n3: \n4: Provides functionality to connect to email servers, search emails,\n5: and retrieve email content.\n6: \n7: Implements TASK-INT1: Email Connector\n8: \"\"\"\n9: \n10: import imaplib\n11: import email as email_lib\n12: from email.header import decode_header\n13: from email.utils import parseaddr, parsedate_to_datetime, getaddresses\n14: from email.message import Message\n15: from typing import List, Dict, Any, Optional\n16: from dataclasses import dataclass, field\n17: from datetime import datetime, timedelta\n18: import logging\n19: import re\n20: \n21: from .base import BaseConnector, ConnectorConfig, SearchResult\n22: \n23: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n24: \n25: \n26: @dataclass\n27: class EmailConfig(ConnectorConfig):\n28:     \"\"\"Configuration for email connector.\"\"\"\n29:     \n30:     # Server settings\n31:     server: str = \"\"\n32:     port: int = 993  # IMAP SSL port\n33:     username: str = \"\"\n34:     password: str = \"\"\n35:     \n36:     # Email-specific settings\n37:     default_folder: str = \"INBOX\"\n38:     max_search_results: int = 50\n39:     snippet_length: int = 200\n40:     \n41:     # Security\n42:     use_ssl: bool = True\n43: \n44: \n45: @dataclass\n46: class EmailSummary:\n47:     \"\"\"Summary information for an email.\"\"\"\n48:     \n49:     id: str                           # Email message ID\n50:     subject: str                      # Email subject\n51:     sender: str                       # Sender email address\n52:     sender_name: str = \"\"             # Sender display name\n53:     date: Optional[datetime] = None   # Date sent\n54:     snippet: str = \"\"                 # Preview of content\n55:     folder: str = \"INBOX\"             # Folder containing the email\n56:     is_read: bool = False             # Read status\n57:     has_attachments: bool = False     # Attachment flag\n58:     flags: List[str] = field(default_factory=list)  # IMAP flags\n59: \n60: \n61: @dataclass\n62: class EmailContent:\n63:     \"\"\"Full content of an email.\"\"\"\n64:     \n65:     id: str                           # Email message ID\n66:     subject: str                      # Email subject\n67:     sender: str                       # Sender email\n68:     sender_name: str = \"\"             # Sender display name\n69:     recipients: List[str] = field(default_factory=list)  # To/Cc recipients\n70:     date: Optional[datetime] = None   # Date sent\n71:     body_text: str = \"\"               # Plain text body\n72:     body_html: str = \"\"               # HTML body (if available)\n73:     attachments: List[Dict] = field(default_factory=list)  # Attachment info\n74:     headers: Dict[str, str] = field(default_factory=dict)  # All headers\n75:     folder: str = \"INBOX\"\n76: \n77: \n78: class EmailConnector(BaseConnector):\n79:     \"\"\"\n80:     Email connector using IMAP protocol.\n81:     \n82:     Connects to email servers via IMAP to search and retrieve emails.\n83:     Supports searching by keywords, date ranges, and folders.\n84:     \n85:     Attributes:\n86:         config: EmailConfig instance\n87:         _client: IMAP client connection\n88:     \n89:     Example:\n90:         >>> # Connect and search emails\n91:         >>> config = EmailConfig(\n92:         ...     server=\"imap.gmail.com\",\n93:         ...     username=\"user@gmail.com\",\n94:         ...     password=\"app_password\"\n95:         ... )\n96:         >>> connector = EmailConnector(config=config)\n97:         >>> \n98:         >>> # Using context manager (auto connect/disconnect)\n99:         >>> with EmailConnector(config=config) as conn:\n100:         ...     results = conn.search(\"project budget\", limit=10)\n101:         ...     for result in results:\n102:         ...         print(f\"{result.title} from {result.metadata['sender']}\")\n103:         ...         \n104:         >>> # Or manual connection\n105:         >>> if connector.connect():\n106:         ...     results = connector.search(\"project budget\")\n107:         ...     connector.disconnect()\n108:     \n109:     Security Notes:\n110:         - Passwords are not stored; use app-specific passwords when possible\n111:         - SSL/TLS is enabled by default\n112:         - Consider using OAuth2 for production use\n113:     \n114:     Performance:\n115:         - Search typically completes in 1-3 seconds\n116:         - Retrieving full content may take longer for large emails\n117:         - Batch operations are more efficient than single retrievals\n118:     \"\"\"\n119:     \n120:     def __init__(self, config: Optional[EmailConfig] = None):\n121:         \"\"\"\n122:         Initialize the email connector.\n123:         \n124:         Args:\n125:             config: EmailConfig instance. Required fields:\n126:                 - server: IMAP server hostname\n127:                 - username: Email username/address\n128:                 - password: Email password or app password\n129:         \"\"\"\n130:         if config is None:\n131:             config = EmailConfig()\n132:         super().__init__(config)\n133:         self.config: EmailConfig = config\n134:         self._client: Optional[imaplib.IMAP4_SSL] = None\n135:         self._current_folder: Optional[str] = None\n136:     \n137:     def connect(self) -> bool:\n138:         \"\"\"\n139:         Establish connection to the IMAP server.\n140:         \n141:         Returns:\n142:             bool: True if connection successful, False otherwise\n143:         \n144:         Raises:\n145:             ValueError: If required configuration is missing\n146:         \"\"\"\n147:         self._clear_error()\n148:         \n149:         # Validate configuration\n150:         if not self.config.server:\n151:             self._set_error(\"Server address is required\")\n152:             return False\n153:         \n154:         if not self.config.username or not self.config.password:\n155:             self._set_error(\"Username and password are required\")\n156:             return False\n157:         \n158:         try:\n159:             logger.info(f\"Connecting to {self.config.server}:{self.config.port}\")\n160:             \n161:             # Create IMAP connection\n162:             if self.config.use_ssl:\n163:                 self._client = imaplib.IMAP4_SSL(\n164:                     self.config.server,\n165:                     self.config.port,\n166:                     timeout=self.config.timeout\n167:                 )\n168:             else:\n169:                 self._client = imaplib.IMAP4(\n170:                     self.config.server,\n171:                     self.config.port,\n172:                     timeout=self.config.timeout\n173:                 )\n174:             \n175:             # Authenticate\n176:             self._client.login(self.config.username, self.config.password)\n177:             self._connected = True\n178:             \n179:             logger.info(f\"Successfully connected to {self.config.server}\")\n180:             return True\n181:             \n182:         except imaplib.IMAP4.error as e:\n183:             self._set_error(f\"IMAP authentication failed: {e}\")\n184:             self._connected = False\n185:             return False\n186:         except Exception as e:\n187:             self._set_error(f\"Connection failed: {e}\")\n188:             self._connected = False\n189:             return False\n190:     \n191:     def disconnect(self) -> bool:\n192:         \"\"\"\n193:         Close the IMAP connection.\n194:         \n195:         Returns:\n196:             bool: True if disconnection successful\n197:         \"\"\"\n198:         try:\n199:             if self._client and self._connected:\n200:                 # Close selected folder\n201:                 try:\n202:                     self._client.close()\n203:                 except:\n204:                     pass\n205:                 \n206:                 # Logout\n207:                 self._client.logout()\n208:                 logger.info(\"Disconnected from email server\")\n209:             \n210:             self._client = None\n211:             self._connected = False\n212:             self._current_folder = None\n213:             return True\n214:             \n215:         except Exception as e:\n216:             logger.warning(f\"Error during disconnect: {e}\")\n217:             self._connected = False\n218:             return True  # Still return True to allow cleanup\n219:     \n220:     def is_connected(self) -> bool:\n221:         \"\"\"\n222:         Check if the IMAP connection is active.\n223:         \n224:         Returns:\n225:             bool: True if connected, False otherwise\n226:         \"\"\"\n227:         if not self._connected or not self._client:\n228:             return False\n229:         \n230:         try:\n231:             # Try a NOOP command to check connection\n232:             self._client.noop()\n233:             return True\n234:         except:\n235:             self._connected = False\n236:             return False\n237:     \n238:     def _select_folder(self, folder: str) -> bool:\n239:         \"\"\"\n240:         Select an IMAP folder for operations.\n241:         \n242:         Args:\n243:             folder: Folder name (e.g., \"INBOX\", \"Sent\", \"Drafts\")\n244:         \n245:         Returns:\n246:             bool: True if folder selected successfully\n247:         \"\"\"\n248:         if not self._connected or not self._client:\n249:             self._set_error(\"Not connected to server\")\n250:             return False\n251:         \n252:         if self._current_folder == folder:\n253:             return True\n254:         \n255:         try:\n256:             status, data = self._client.select(folder)\n257:             if status == 'OK':\n258:                 self._current_folder = folder\n259:                 return True\n260:             else:\n261:                 self._set_error(f\"Failed to select folder: {folder}\")\n262:                 return False\n263:         except Exception as e:\n264:             self._set_error(f\"Error selecting folder: {e}\")\n265:             return False\n266:     \n267:     def search(\n268:         self,\n269:         query: str,\n270:         limit: int = 10,\n271:         filters: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n272:         folders: Optional[List[str]] = None,\n273:         **kwargs\n274:     ) -> List[SearchResult]:\n275:         \"\"\"\n276:         Search for emails matching the query.\n277:         \n278:         Args:\n279:             query: Search query (keywords or phrases)\n280:             limit: Maximum number of results (default: 10)\n281:             filters: Optional filters:\n282:                 - date_from: Start date (datetime or str \"YYYY-MM-DD\")\n283:                 - date_to: End date (datetime or str \"YYYY-MM-DD\")\n284:                 - sender: Filter by sender email\n285:                 - unread_only: Only return unread emails\n286:             folders: List of folders to search (default: [\"INBOX\"])\n287:             **kwargs: Additional parameters (ignored)\n288:         \n289:         Returns:\n290:             List of SearchResult objects for matching emails\n291:         \n292:         Example:\n293:             >>> results = connector.search(\n294:             ...     \"project budget\",\n295:             ...     limit=5,\n296:             ...     filters={'date_from': '2024-01-01'},\n297:             ...     folders=[\"INBOX\", \"Sent\"]\n298:             ... )\n299:         \"\"\"\n300:         if not self._connected or not self._client:\n301:             self._set_error(\"Not connected to server\")\n302:             return []\n303:         \n304:         if not query or not query.strip():\n305:             logger.warning(\"Empty search query\")\n306:             return []\n307:         \n308:         self._clear_error()\n309:         folders = folders or [self.config.default_folder]\n310:         all_results = []\n311:         \n312:         for folder in folders:\n313:             if not self._select_folder(folder):\n314:                 continue\n315:             \n316:             # Build IMAP search criteria\n317:             criteria = self._build_search_criteria(query, filters)\n318:             \n319:             try:\n320:                 # Search for matching messages\n321:                 status, message_ids = self._client.search(None, *criteria)\n322:                 \n323:                 if status != 'OK':\n324:                     logger.warning(f\"Search failed in folder {folder}\")\n325:                     continue\n326:                 \n327:                 # Get message IDs\n328:                 ids = message_ids[0].split()\n329:                 \n330:                 # Limit results per folder\n331:                 ids = ids[-limit:] if len(ids) > limit else ids\n332:                 \n333:                 # Fetch summaries for each message\n334:                 for msg_id in ids:\n335:                     try:\n336:                         summary = self._fetch_email_summary(msg_id, folder)\n337:                         if summary:\n338:                             all_results.append(self._summary_to_search_result(summary))\n339:                     except Exception as e:\n340:                         logger.warning(f\"Error fetching email {msg_id}: {e}\")\n341:                 \n342:             except Exception as e:\n343:                 self._set_error(f\"Search error in {folder}: {e}\")\n344:                 continue\n345:         \n346:         # Sort by date (newest first)\n347:         all_results.sort(\n348:             key=lambda r: r.timestamp or datetime.min,\n349:             reverse=True\n350:         )\n351:         \n352:         return all_results[:limit]\n353:     \n354:     def _build_search_criteria(\n355:         self,\n356:         query: str,\n357:         filters: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n358:     ) -> List[str]:\n359:         \"\"\"\n360:         Build IMAP search criteria from query and filters.\n361:         \n362:         Args:\n363:             query: Search query\n364:             filters: Optional filters\n365:         \n366:         Returns:\n367:             List of IMAP search criteria strings\n368:         \"\"\"\n369:         criteria = []\n370:         \n371:         # Add query terms (OR all terms)\n372:         terms = query.split()\n373:         if len(terms) == 1:\n374:             criteria.extend(['SUBJECT', terms[0]])\n375:         else:\n376:             # For multiple terms, search in subject or body\n377:             for term in terms:\n378:                 criteria.extend(['OR', 'SUBJECT', term, 'BODY', term])\n379:         \n380:         # Add filters\n381:         if filters:\n382:             # Date range\n383:             if 'date_from' in filters:\n384:                 date_from = filters['date_from']\n385:                 if isinstance(date_from, datetime):\n386:                     date_str = date_from.strftime('%d-%b-%Y')\n387:                 else:\n388:                     date_str = datetime.strptime(date_from, '%Y-%m-%d').strftime('%d-%b-%Y')\n389:                 criteria.extend(['SINCE', date_str])\n390:             \n391:             if 'date_to' in filters:\n392:                 date_to = filters['date_to']\n393:                 if isinstance(date_to, datetime):\n394:                     date_str = date_to.strftime('%d-%b-%Y')\n395:                 else:\n396:                     date_str = datetime.strptime(date_to, '%Y-%m-%d').strftime('%d-%b-%Y')\n397:                 criteria.extend(['BEFORE', date_str])\n398:             \n399:             # Sender filter\n400:             if 'sender' in filters:\n401:                 criteria.extend(['FROM', filters['sender']])\n402:             \n403:             # Unread only\n404:             if filters.get('unread_only'):\n405:                 criteria.append('UNSEEN')\n406:         \n407:         # If no criteria, match all\n408:         if not criteria:\n409:             criteria = ['ALL']\n410:         \n411:         return criteria\n412:     \n413:     def _fetch_email_summary(\n414:         self,\n415:         msg_id: bytes,\n416:         folder: str\n417:     ) -> Optional[EmailSummary]:\n418:         \"\"\"\n419:         Fetch summary information for an email.\n420:         \n421:         Args:\n422:             msg_id: IMAP message ID\n423:             folder: Folder name\n424:         \n425:         Returns:\n426:             EmailSummary or None if fetch fails\n427:         \"\"\"\n428:         if not self._client:\n429:             return None\n430:         \n431:         try:\n432:             # Fetch headers and flags\n433:             status, data = self._client.fetch(\n434:                 msg_id,\n435:                 '(FLAGS BODY.PEEK[HEADER])'\n436:             )\n437:             \n438:             if status != 'OK':\n439:                 return None\n440:             \n441:             # Parse the response\n442:             response = data[0]\n443:             flags = []\n444:             raw_headers = b''\n445:             \n446:             if isinstance(response, tuple):\n447:                 flags_str = response[0].decode()\n448:                 raw_headers = response[1]\n449:                 # Extract flags\n450:                 if '\\\\Seen' in flags_str:\n451:                     flags.append('seen')\n452:                 if '\\\\Flagged' in flags_str:\n453:                     flags.append('flagged')\n454:                 if '\\\\Answered' in flags_str:\n455:                     flags.append('answered')\n456:             else:\n457:                 raw_headers = response\n458:             \n459:             # Parse email headers\n460:             msg = email_lib.message_from_bytes(raw_headers)\n461:             \n462:             # Decode subject\n463:             subject = self._decode_header(msg.get('Subject', '(No Subject)'))\n464:             \n465:             # Parse sender\n466:             sender_name, sender_email = parseaddr(msg.get('From', ''))\n467:             \n468:             # Parse date\n469:             date_str = msg.get('Date', '')\n470:             date = None\n471:             if date_str:\n472:                 try:\n473:                     date = parsedate_to_datetime(date_str)\n474:                 except:\n475:                     pass\n476:             \n477:             # Check for attachments\n478:             has_attachments = self._check_attachments(msg)\n479:             \n480:             # Fetch snippet from body\n481:             snippet = self._fetch_snippet(msg_id)\n482:             \n483:             return EmailSummary(\n484:                 id=msg_id.decode(),\n485:                 subject=subject,\n486:                 sender=sender_email,\n487:                 sender_name=sender_name,\n488:                 date=date,\n489:                 snippet=snippet[:self.config.snippet_length],\n490:                 folder=folder,\n491:                 is_read='seen' in flags,\n492:                 has_attachments=has_attachments,\n493:                 flags=flags\n494:             )\n495:             \n496:         except Exception as e:\n497:             logger.error(f\"Error fetching email summary: {e}\")\n498:             return None\n499:     \n500:     def _fetch_snippet(self, msg_id: bytes) -> str:\n501:         \"\"\"\n502:         Fetch a text snippet from the email body.\n503:         \n504:         Args:\n505:             msg_id: IMAP message ID\n506:         \n507:         Returns:\n508:             str: Text snippet\n509:         \"\"\"\n510:         if not self._client:\n511:             return \"\"\n512:         \n513:         try:\n514:             status, data = self._client.fetch(\n515:                 msg_id,\n516:                 '(BODY.PEEK[TEXT])'\n517:             )\n518:             \n519:             if status != 'OK':\n520:                 return \"\"\n521:             \n522:             body = data[0][1] if isinstance(data[0], tuple) else data[0]\n523:             \n524:             # Try to decode\n525:             try:\n526:                 text = body.decode('utf-8', errors='ignore')\n527:             except:\n528:                 text = body.decode('latin-1', errors='ignore')\n529:             \n530:             # Clean HTML tags if present\n531:             text = re.sub(r'<[^>]+>', '', text)\n532:             # Normalize whitespace\n533:             text = ' '.join(text.split())\n534:             \n535:             return text\n536:             \n537:         except Exception as e:\n538:             logger.warning(f\"Error fetching snippet: {e}\")\n539:             return \"\"\n540:     \n541:     def _check_attachments(self, msg: Message) -> bool:\n542:         \"\"\"Check if email has attachments.\"\"\"\n543:         for part in msg.walk():\n544:             if part.get_content_disposition() == 'attachment':\n545:                 return True\n546:         return False\n547:     \n548:     def _decode_header(self, header: str) -> str:\n549:         \"\"\"Decode an email header with proper encoding.\"\"\"\n550:         if not header:\n551:             return \"\"\n552:         \n553:         decoded_parts = []\n554:         for part, charset in decode_header(header):\n555:             if isinstance(part, bytes):\n556:                 charset = charset or 'utf-8'\n557:                 try:\n558:                     decoded_parts.append(part.decode(charset, errors='ignore'))\n559:                 except:\n560:                     decoded_parts.append(part.decode('utf-8', errors='ignore'))\n561:             else:\n562:                 decoded_parts.append(str(part))\n563:         \n564:         return ' '.join(decoded_parts)\n565:     \n566:     def _summary_to_search_result(self, summary: EmailSummary) -> SearchResult:\n567:         \"\"\"Convert EmailSummary to SearchResult.\"\"\"\n568:         return SearchResult(\n569:             id=summary.id,\n570:             title=summary.subject,\n571:             snippet=summary.snippet,\n572:             source='email',\n573:             metadata={\n574:                 'sender': summary.sender,\n575:                 'sender_name': summary.sender_name,\n576:                 'folder': summary.folder,\n577:                 'is_read': summary.is_read,\n578:                 'has_attachments': summary.has_attachments,\n579:                 'flags': summary.flags\n580:             },\n581:             timestamp=summary.date\n582:         )\n583:     \n584:     def get_by_id(self, id: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]:\n585:         \"\"\"\n586:         Retrieve the full content of an email by its ID.\n587:         \n588:         Args:\n589:             id: Email message ID\n590:         \n591:         Returns:\n592:             Dict containing the full email content, or None if not found\n593:         \n594:         Example:\n595:             >>> email = connector.get_by_id(\"123\")\n596:             >>> if email:\n597:             ...     print(f\"Subject: {email['subject']}\")\n598:             ...     print(f\"Body: {email['body_text'][:100]}...\")\n599:         \"\"\"\n600:         if not self._connected or not self._client:\n601:             self._set_error(\"Not connected to server\")\n602:             return None\n603:         \n604:         self._clear_error()\n605:         \n606:         try:\n607:             # Fetch the full email\n608:             status, data = self._client.fetch(id.encode(), '(RFC822)')\n609:             \n610:             if status != 'OK':\n611:                 self._set_error(f\"Failed to fetch email {id}\")\n612:                 return None\n613:             \n614:             # Parse the email\n615:             raw_email = data[0][1] if isinstance(data[0], tuple) else data[0]\n616:             msg = email_lib.message_from_bytes(raw_email)\n617:             \n618:             # Extract body text and HTML\n619:             body_text = \"\"\n620:             body_html = \"\"\n621:             attachments = []\n622:             \n623:             for part in msg.walk():\n624:                 content_type = part.get_content_type()\n625:                 content_disposition = str(part.get('Content-Disposition', ''))\n626:                 \n627:                 if 'attachment' in content_disposition:\n628:                     # Handle attachment\n629:                     filename = part.get_filename()\n630:                     if filename:\n631:                         attachments.append({\n632:                             'filename': self._decode_header(filename),\n633:                             'content_type': content_type,\n634:                             'size': len(part.get_payload(decode=True) or b'')\n635:                         })\n636:                 elif content_type == 'text/plain' and not body_text:\n637:                     payload = part.get_payload(decode=True)\n638:                     if payload:\n639:                         charset = part.get_content_charset() or 'utf-8'\n640:                         body_text = payload.decode(charset, errors='ignore')\n641:                 elif content_type == 'text/html' and not body_html:\n642:                     payload = part.get_payload(decode=True)\n643:                     if payload:\n644:                         charset = part.get_content_charset() or 'utf-8'\n645:                         body_html = payload.decode(charset, errors='ignore')\n646:             \n647:             # Extract recipients\n648:             recipients = []\n649:             for header in ['To', 'Cc', 'Bcc']:\n650:                 value = msg.get(header, '')\n651:                 if value:\n652:                     for name, addr in getaddresses([value]):\n653:                         if addr:\n654:                             recipients.append(addr)\n655:             \n656:             # Extract headers\n657:             headers = {}\n658:             for key in msg.keys():\n659:                 headers[key] = self._decode_header(msg.get(key, ''))\n660:             \n661:             # Parse date\n662:             date_str = msg.get('Date', '')\n663:             date = None\n664:             if date_str:\n665:                 try:\n666:                     date = parsedate_to_datetime(date_str)\n667:                 except:\n668:                     pass\n669:             \n670:             return {\n671:                 'id': id,\n672:                 'subject': self._decode_header(msg.get('Subject', '')),\n673:                 'sender': parseaddr(msg.get('From', ''))[1],\n674:                 'sender_name': parseaddr(msg.get('From', ''))[0],\n675:                 'recipients': recipients,\n676:                 'date': date,\n677:                 'body_text': body_text,\n678:                 'body_html': body_html,\n679:                 'attachments': attachments,\n680:                 'headers': headers,\n681:                 'folder': self._current_folder or 'INBOX'\n682:             }\n683:             \n684:         except Exception as e:\n685:             self._set_error(f\"Error retrieving email: {e}\")\n686:             return None\n687:     \n688:     def list_folders(self) -> List[str]:\n689:         \"\"\"\n690:         List all available folders/mailboxes.\n691:         \n692:         Returns:\n693:             List of folder names\n694:         \"\"\"\n695:         if not self._connected or not self._client:\n696:             self._set_error(\"Not connected to server\")\n697:             return []\n698:         \n699:         try:\n700:             status, folders = self._client.list()\n701:             if status != 'OK':\n702:                 return []\n703:             \n704:             folder_names = []\n705:             for folder in folders:\n706:                 if folder:\n707:                     # Parse folder name from IMAP LIST response\n708:                     parts = folder.decode().split('\"')\n709:                     if len(parts) >= 3:\n710:                         folder_names.append(parts[-2])\n711:             \n712:             return folder_names\n713:             \n714:         except Exception as e:\n715:             self._set_error(f\"Error listing folders: {e}\")\n716:             return []\n717:     \n718:     def get_recent_emails(\n719:         self,\n720:         folder: str = \"INBOX\",\n721:         count: int = 10\n722:     ) -> List[EmailSummary]:\n723:         \"\"\"\n724:         Get the most recent emails from a folder.\n725:         \n726:         Args:\n727:             folder: Folder name (default: \"INBOX\")\n728:             count: Number of recent emails to retrieve\n729:         \n730:         Returns:\n731:             List of EmailSummary objects\n732:         \"\"\"\n733:         if not self._connected or not self._client:\n734:             self._set_error(\"Not connected to server\")\n735:             return []\n736:         \n737:         if not self._select_folder(folder):\n738:             return []\n739:         \n740:         try:\n741:             # Search for all messages\n742:             status, message_ids = self._client.search(None, 'ALL')\n743:             \n744:             if status != 'OK':\n745:                 return []\n746:             \n747:             ids = message_ids[0].split()\n748:             # Get the most recent ones\n749:             ids = ids[-count:] if len(ids) > count else ids\n750:             \n751:             summaries = []\n752:             for msg_id in reversed(ids):  # Newest first\n753:                 summary = self._fetch_email_summary(msg_id, folder)\n754:                 if summary:\n755:                     summaries.append(summary)\n756:             \n757:             return summaries\n758:             \n759:         except Exception as e:\n760:             self._set_error(f\"Error getting recent emails: {e}\")\n761:             return []\n\n(End of file - total 761 lines)\n</content>","title":"scripts/connectors/email.py","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"\nEmail connector implementation using IMAP protocol.\n\nProvides functionality to connect to email servers, search emails,\nand retrieve email content.\n\nImplements TASK-INT1: Email Connector\n\"\"\"\n\nimport imaplib\nimport email as email_lib\nfrom email.header import decode_header\nfrom email.utils import parseaddr, parsedate_to_datetime, getaddresses\nfrom email.message import Message\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Any, Optional\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta\nimport logging\nimport re\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1772871940100,"end":1772871940105}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772871940405,"sessionID":"ses_3389967ebffeq10PXnV18VW536","part":{"id":"prt_cc766f932001cFXQScR2ypDlNE","sessionID":"ses_3389967ebffeq10PXnV18VW536","messageID":"msg_cc766dbfc001kuS2zx2X5TvzeS","type":"tool","callID":"call_8c34cbba720048379799e437","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/sonnet/opencode/SG-AgentTeam/scripts/connectors/base.py"},"output":"<path>/Users/sonnet/opencode/SG-AgentTeam/scripts/connectors/base.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: \"\"\"\n2: Base connector abstract class for external data sources.\n3: \n4: Defines the interface that all connectors must implement.\n5: \"\"\"\n6: \n7: from abc import ABC, abstractmethod\n8: from typing import List, Dict, Any, Optional\n9: from dataclasses import dataclass\n10: from datetime import datetime\n11: import logging\n12: \n13: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n14: \n15: \n16: @dataclass\n17: class ConnectorConfig:\n18:     \"\"\"Base configuration for connectors.\"\"\"\n19:     \n20:     # Connection settings\n21:     timeout: int = 30\n22:     retry_count: int = 3\n23:     retry_delay: float = 1.0\n24:     \n25:     # Security settings\n26:     verify_ssl: bool = True\n27:     use_tls: bool = True\n28: \n29: \n30: @dataclass\n31: class SearchResult:\n32:     \"\"\"Standard search result from any connector.\"\"\"\n33:     \n34:     id: str                           # Unique identifier\n35:     title: str                        # Result title/subject\n36:     snippet: str                      # Brief content preview\n37:     source: str                       # Source identifier (e.g., 'email', 'database')\n38:     metadata: Dict[str, Any]          # Additional metadata\n39:     timestamp: Optional[datetime] = None  # Creation/modification time\n40:     score: Optional[float] = None     # Relevance score (if applicable)\n41: \n42: \n43: class BaseConnector(ABC):\n44:     \"\"\"\n45:     Abstract base class for all data source connectors.\n46:     \n47:     All connectors must implement the following methods:\n48:     - connect(): Establish connection to the data source\n49:     - disconnect(): Close the connection\n50:     - is_connected(): Check if connection is active\n51:     - search(): Search for data in the source\n52:     \n53:     The connector pattern ensures consistent API across different\n54:     data sources (email, databases, APIs, etc.).\n55:     \n56:     Attributes:\n57:         config: Connector configuration\n58:         _connected: Internal connection state flag\n59:     \n60:     Example:\n61:         >>> class MyConnector(BaseConnector):\n62:         ...     def connect(self) -> bool:\n63:         ...         # Implementation\n64:         ...         pass\n65:         ...\n66:         >>> connector = MyConnector(config=ConnectorConfig())\n67:         >>> if connector.connect():\n68:         ...     results = connector.search(\"query\")\n69:         ...     connector.disconnect()\n70:     \"\"\"\n71:     \n72:     def __init__(self, config: Optional[ConnectorConfig] = None):\n73:         \"\"\"\n74:         Initialize the connector.\n75:         \n76:         Args:\n77:             config: Optional configuration object. If None, uses defaults.\n78:         \"\"\"\n79:         self.config = config or ConnectorConfig()\n80:         self._connected = False\n81:         self._last_error: Optional[str] = None\n82:     \n83:     @abstractmethod\n84:     def connect(self) -> bool:\n85:         \"\"\"\n86:         Establish connection to the data source.\n87:         \n88:         This method should:\n89:         1. Validate configuration\n90:         2. Establish the connection\n91:         3. Set _connected = True on success\n92:         4. Set _last_error on failure\n93:         \n94:         Returns:\n95:             bool: True if connection successful, False otherwise\n96:         \n97:         Raises:\n98:             ConnectionError: If connection fails after all retries\n99:         \n100:         Example:\n101:             >>> connector = EmailConnector(server=\"imap.gmail.com\", ...)\n102:             >>> success = connector.connect()\n103:             >>> if not success:\n104:             ...     print(connector.get_last_error())\n105:         \"\"\"\n106:         pass\n107:     \n108:     @abstractmethod\n109:     def disconnect(self) -> bool:\n110:         \"\"\"\n111:         Close the connection to the data source.\n112:         \n113:         This method should:\n114:         1. Close any open connections\n115:         2. Clean up resources\n116:         3. Set _connected = False\n117:         \n118:         Returns:\n119:             bool: True if disconnection successful, False otherwise\n120:         \n121:         Example:\n122:             >>> connector.disconnect()\n123:             True\n124:         \"\"\"\n125:         pass\n126:     \n127:     @abstractmethod\n128:     def is_connected(self) -> bool:\n129:         \"\"\"\n130:         Check if the connection is currently active.\n131:         \n132:         Returns:\n133:             bool: True if connected, False otherwise\n134:         \n135:         Example:\n136:             >>> if connector.is_connected():\n137:             ...     results = connector.search(\"query\")\n138:         \"\"\"\n139:         pass\n140:     \n141:     @abstractmethod\n142:     def search(\n143:         self,\n144:         query: str,\n145:         limit: int = 10,\n146:         filters: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n147:         **kwargs\n148:     ) -> List[SearchResult]:\n149:         \"\"\"\n150:         Search for data in the connected source.\n151:         \n152:         Args:\n153:             query: Search query string\n154:             limit: Maximum number of results to return (default: 10)\n155:             filters: Optional filters to narrow results\n156:                 Example: {'folder': 'INBOX', 'date_from': '2024-01-01'}\n157:             **kwargs: Additional connector-specific parameters\n158:         \n159:         Returns:\n160:             List of SearchResult objects matching the query\n161:         \n162:         Raises:\n163:             ConnectionError: If not connected\n164:             ValueError: If query is invalid\n165:         \n166:         Example:\n167:             >>> results = connector.search(\"project budget\", limit=5)\n168:             >>> for result in results:\n169:             ...     print(f\"{result.title}: {result.snippet}\")\n170:         \"\"\"\n171:         pass\n172:     \n173:     @abstractmethod\n174:     def get_by_id(self, id: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]:\n175:         \"\"\"\n176:         Retrieve a specific item by its unique identifier.\n177:         \n178:         Args:\n179:             id: Unique identifier of the item\n180:         \n181:         Returns:\n182:             Dict containing the full item data, or None if not found\n183:         \n184:         Example:\n185:             >>> email = connector.get_by_id(\"msg_123\")\n186:             >>> if email:\n187:             ...     print(email['body'])\n188:         \"\"\"\n189:         pass\n190:     \n191:     def get_last_error(self) -> Optional[str]:\n192:         \"\"\"\n193:         Get the last error message.\n194:         \n195:         Returns:\n196:             str or None: Last error message, or None if no error\n197:         \"\"\"\n198:         return self._last_error\n199:     \n200:     def _set_error(self, message: str) -> None:\n201:         \"\"\"Set the last error message.\"\"\"\n202:         self._last_error = message\n203:         logger.error(f\"[{self.__class__.__name__}] {message}\")\n204:     \n205:     def _clear_error(self) -> None:\n206:         \"\"\"Clear the last error message.\"\"\"\n207:         self._last_error = None\n208:     \n209:     def __enter__(self):\n210:         \"\"\"Context manager entry - connect automatically.\"\"\"\n211:         self.connect()\n212:         return self\n213:     \n214:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb):\n215:         \"\"\"Context manager exit - disconnect automatically.\"\"\"\n216:         self.disconnect()\n217:         return False\n218:     \n219:     def __repr__(self) -> str:\n220:         \"\"\"String representation of the connector.\"\"\"\n221:         status = \"connected\" if self._connected else \"disconnected\"\n222:         return f\"{self.__class__.__name__}({status})\"\n\n(End of file - total 222 lines)\n</content>","title":"scripts/connectors/base.py","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"\nBase connector abstract class for external data sources.\n\nDefines the interface that all connectors must implement.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom abc import ABC, abstractmethod\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Any, Optional\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom datetime import datetime\nimport logging\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass ConnectorConfig:\n    \"\"\"Base configuration for connectors.\"\"\"\n    \n    # Connection settings","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1772871940403,"end":1772871940404}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772871940782,"sessionID":"ses_3389967ebffeq10PXnV18VW536","part":{"id":"prt_cc766faa50018ys517WJBWuGQU","sessionID":"ses_3389967ebffeq10PXnV18VW536","messageID":"msg_cc766dbfc001kuS2zx2X5TvzeS","type":"tool","callID":"call_265f8eb412d24cf79bf11433","tool":"glob","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"**/extraction.py"},"output":"No files found","title":"","metadata":{"count":0,"truncated":false},"time":{"start":1772871940774,"end":1772871940781}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772871941224,"sessionID":"ses_3389967ebffeq10PXnV18VW536","part":{"id":"prt_cc766fc65001t3Y7QxvWeCIGDh","sessionID":"ses_3389967ebffeq10PXnV18VW536","messageID":"msg_cc766dbfc001kuS2zx2X5TvzeS","type":"tool","callID":"call_15376c8708b6452082be64f9","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/sonnet/opencode/SG-AgentTeam/README.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/sonnet/opencode/SG-AgentTeam/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: # Agent Team Framework\n2: \n3: > 🤝 基于文档的AI Agent协作框架\n4: \n5: **版本**: v1.1 | **状态**: 实践验证中 | **更新**: 2026-03-07\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## 💡 核心理念\n10: \n11: 让多个AI Agent像人类团队一样**高效、可靠地协作**——通过**文档化交互**实现异步、可追溯、可自动化的协作模式。\n12: \n13: ## 📚 研究框架\n14: \n15: 本项目使用 **[SEARCH-R Framework](https://github.com/Sonnet0524/SEARCH-R)** 进行系统性研究。\n16: \n17: SEARCH-R是一个通用的研究型Agent框架，提供：\n18: - 🔍 **SEARCH-R方法论** - 完整的研究循环\n19: - 🤖 **Research Agent模板** - 可复用的研究Agent\n20: - 📄 **标准文档模板** - 研究文档的标准格式\n21: - 🛠️ **Skills库** - 可复用的研究能力\n22: \n23: **框架仓库**: [https://github.com/Sonnet0524/SEARCH-R](https://github.com/Sonnet0524/SEARCH-R)\n24: \n25: ---\n26: \n27: ## 📖 内容导航\n28: \n29: 本仓库包含两部分内容：\n30: \n31: | 部分 | 内容 | 适合读者 |\n32: |------|------|---------|\n33: | **[框架篇](#-框架篇)** | 理论、方法论、设计思想 | 想了解Agent协作模式的研究者 |\n34: | **[实践篇](#-实践篇)** | 本项目的Agent Team实现 | 想参考具体实现的实践者 |\n35: \n36: ### 🔬 研究文档\n37: \n38: 完整的研究成果位于 [docs/research/](docs/research/)\n39: \n40: | 研究课题 | 核心成果 | 状态 |\n41: |---------|---------|------|\n42: | [SEARCH-R方法论](agents/research/CATCH_UP.md) | 研究型Agent工作循环 | ✅ 方法论确立 |\n43: | [Agent四层架构](agents/research/CATCH_UP.md) | 身份+能力+记忆+访问系统 | ✅ 理论突破 |\n44: | [质量门控分层](agents/research/CATCH_UP.md) | 元认知+规则+工具三层 | ✅ 理论突破 |\n45: | [质量门控理论](docs/research/quality-gates/) | Human介入触发器 | ✅ 理论突破 |\n46: | [Agent社会架构](docs/research/agent-society/) | Agent定义标准 | ✅ 基础完成 |\n47: | [Agent交互模式](docs/research/agent-interaction/) | 文档化交互 | ✅ 核心成果 |\n48: | [Agent模板标准](docs/research/agent-template-standard/) | Agent行为规范 | 🔜 待研讨 |\n49: \n50: 📄 **完整研究过程**: [研究日志](docs/research/research-log.md)\n51: \n52: ---\n53: \n54: # 🎓 框架篇\n55: \n56: > 通用理论，可复用于任何Agent协作场景\n57: \n58: ## 🎯 核心研究\n59: \n60: ### SEARCH-R方法论 ⭐ 最新突破\n61: \n62: **方法论确立**: 研究型Agent的标准工作循环\n63: \n64: ```\n65: SEARCH-R方法论\n66: \n67: S - Survey（观察调研）\n68: E - Explore（探索检索）\n69: A - Analyze（分析思考）\n70: R - Review（评审探讨）\n71: C - Confirm（确认验证）\n72: H - Harvest（收获产出）\n73: R - Reflect（反思迭代）\n74: \n75: 循环：S → E → A → R → C → H → R → (回到S)\n76: ```\n77: \n78: **命名由来**: Search（搜索）+ Reflect（反思）= 持续探索真理\n79: \n80: **核心价值**:\n81: - 🔍 **观察调研** - 从实践中发现问题\n82: - 📚 **探索检索** - 检索相关知识\n83: - 💭 **分析思考** - 深度理论构建\n84: - 🤝 **评审探讨** - Human参与探讨\n85: - ✅ **确认验证** - 实践中验证\n86: - 📦 **收获产出** - 沉淀研究成果\n87: - 🔄 **反思迭代** - 持续优化方法\n88: \n89: 📖 [完整方法论](agents/research/CATCH_UP.md)\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ### Agent交互模式 ⭐ 核心成果\n94: \n95: **研究问题**: Agent之间如何高效、可靠地交互？\n96: \n97: **解决方案**: 基于文档的上下文交换机制\n98: \n99: ```\n100: 传统方式：Agent ←→ Agent（直接对话）\n101:            ↓ 问题：同步阻塞、不可追溯、难以自动化\n102: \n103: 本研究：Agent ←→ 文档 ←→ Agent（文档中介）\n104:            ↓ 优势：异步协作、可追溯、可自动化\n105: ```\n106: \n107: **核心成果**:\n108: - 📄 **文档化交互协议** - 标准化的交互格式和状态流转\n109: - 📁 **分层文档体系** - Level 0/1/2按需加载\n110: - 🚀 **Message Queue愿景** - 未来可实现全自动协作\n111: \n112: **效果数据**:\n113: \n114: | 指标 | 传统方式 | 本框架 | 改进 |\n115: |------|---------|--------|------|\n116: | Context使用 | 600行 | 40行 | ↓93% |\n117: | 协作冲突 | 每周3次 | 0次 | ↓100% |\n118: | 预测准确率 | 50% | 85% | ↑70% |\n119: \n120: 📖 [深入研究](docs/research/agent-interaction/)\n121: \n122: ---\n123: \n124: ## 🔥 最新理论突破\n125: \n126: ### Agent系统四层架构\n127: \n128: **研究突破**: Agent系统的完整架构定义\n129: \n130: ```\n131: Agent系统 = 身份层 + 能力系统 + 记忆系统 + 访问系统\n132: \n133: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n134: │ 身份层（AGENTS.md）                      │\n135: │ - 角色定义                              │\n136: │ - 核心能力（不可分离）                   │\n137: │ - 元认知意识                            │\n138: └─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n139:          ↓\n140: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n141: │ 能力系统                                │\n142: │ - 核心能力：定义在AGENTS.md中           │\n143: │ - 通用能力：Skills，可复用、按需加载     │\n144: └─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n145:          ↓\n146: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n147: │ 记忆系统                                │\n148: │ - 身份记忆：AGENTS.md                   │\n149: │ - 状态记忆：CATCH_UP.md                 │\n150: │ - 经验记忆：experiences/                │\n151: │ - 会话记忆：session-log.md              │\n152: └─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n153:          ↓\n154: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n155: │ 访问系统                                │\n156: │ - 记忆索引：memory-index.yaml           │\n157: │ - 检索机制：按需加载                     │\n158: │ - 压缩机制：短期→长期                    │\n159: └─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n160: ```\n161: \n162: **关键洞察**:\n163: - 🎯 **记忆 ≠ 访问** - 记忆是内容，索引是方法\n164: - 🔧 **核心能力不分离** - 定义在AGENTS.md中\n165: - 📦 **Skills可复用** - 通用能力按需加载\n166: \n167: ---\n168: \n169: ### 质量门控分层定义\n170: \n171: **研究突破**: 质量门控的三层结构\n172: \n173: ```\n174: 质量门控 = 元认知意识 + 评估规则 + 评估工具\n175: \n176: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n177: │ 元认知意识（不可分离）                   │\n178: │ - \"我知道自己什么时候不知道\"            │\n179: │ - Agent的核心属性                       │\n180: │ - 定义在AGENTS.md中                     │\n181: └─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n182:          ↓\n183: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n184: │ 评估规则（可Skills化）                  │\n185: │ - 确定性判断规则                        │\n186: │ - 可接受性判断规则                      │\n187: │ - 混淆判断规则                          │\n188: └─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n189:          ↓\n190: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n191: │ 评估工具（可Skills化）                  │\n192: │ - 质量门控Schema                        │\n193: │ - 评估流程                              │\n194: │ - 可复用的工具                          │\n195: └─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n196: ```\n197: \n198: **关键区分**:\n199: - 🧠 元认知意识 → Agent核心属性（不分离）\n200: - 📋 评估规则 → 可Skills化（按需加载）\n201: - 🛠️ 评估工具 → 可Skills化（可复用）\n202: \n203: ---\n204: \n205: ### Agent vs Subagent正确定义\n206: \n207: **研究突破**: 以决策自主性为区分标准\n208: \n209: ```\n210: 区分标准：决策自主性（不是文档完整性）\n211: \n212: Agent（有自主权）:\n213:   ✅ 可以自主决策\n214:   ✅ 独立的任务空间\n215:   ✅ 对结果负责\n216:   示例：PM Agent、Research Agent\n217: \n218: Subagent（无自主权）:\n219:   ✅ 任务绑定\n220:   ✅ 决策受限\n221:   ✅ 执行分配的任务\n222:   示例：AI Team、Core Team、Integration Team\n223: ```\n224: \n225: **关键洞察**: 不是\"有没有文档\"决定Agent vs Subagent，而是\"有没有自主权\"\n226: \n227: ---\n228: \n229: ### Skills分离原则\n230: \n231: **研究突破**: 能力分离的三大原则\n232: \n233: ```\n234: 原则1：非每次都需要 → 可以Skills化\n235: 原则2：可多个Agent复用 → 应该Skills化\n236: 原则3：相对独立的能力单元 → 可以Skills化\n237: \n238: Skills分类：\n239: ├─ 决策支持类：quality-gate、risk-assessment\n240: ├─ 工作流类：git-workflow、review-process\n241: ├─ 规范类：coding-standards、documentation-guide\n242: └─ 领域知识类：embedding-models、vector-search\n243: ```\n244: \n245: **AGENTS.md精简原则**: 只保留身份 + 核心能力，目标 ~5k tokens\n246: \n247: ---\n248: \n249: ### 质量门控 = Human介入触发器\n250: \n251: **研究突破**: 质量门控的本质重新定义\n252: \n253: ```\n254: 旧理解：能力边界声明（Agent间协作）\n255: 新理解：Human介入触发器（PM自主决策边界）\n256: ```\n257: \n258: **核心价值**:\n259: - 🎯 **确定性评估** - 判断结果是否确定\n260: - ✅ **可接受性评估** - 判断结果是否可接受\n261: - 🔍 **混淆判断** - 判断是否存在理解偏差\n262: - 👤 **Human介入决策** - 决定何时呼叫Human\n263: \n264: **工作机制**:\n265: ```\n266: Agent输出 → PM评估\n267: ├─ 确定性HIGH + 可接受性HIGH + 无混淆 → PM自主决策\n268: └─ 确定性LOW 或 可接受性LOW 或 存在混淆 → 呼叫Human\n269: ```\n270: \n271: **Token效率**: ~15 tokens实现关键决策机制\n272: \n273: 📖 [完整研究过程](docs/research/research-log.md)\n274: \n275: ---\n276: \n277: ### Agent社会架构理论\n278: \n279: **研究问题**: 如何定义Agent vs Subagent？如何设计Agent社会架构？\n280: \n281: **核心定义**:\n282: \n283: | 类型 | 生命周期 | 存在方式 | 创建者 |\n284: |------|---------|---------|--------|\n285: | **Agent** | 持久（Persistent） | Serve模式 | System/PM |\n286: | **Subagent** | 临时（Transient） | Task-bound | Agent |\n287: \n288: **关键洞察**: 差异在于**生命周期**，不在能力高低\n289: \n290: **PM Agent模型**:\n291: ```\n292: PM能力 = LLM能力 + Prompt设计 + 经验积累\n293: 真正价值 = 最优协调（而非最强能力）\n294: 决策边界 = 质量门控判断\n295: ```\n296: \n297: 📖 [调研报告](docs/research/agent-team-design-survey.md) | [执行摘要](docs/research/agent-team-design-survey-summary.md)\n298: \n299: ---\n300: \n301: ### 框架本质重新定位\n302: \n303: **理论突破**:\n304: \n305: ```\n306: 从：\"人机协作框架\" → Human是核心参与者\n307: 到：\"多智能体协同框架\" → Human是最小化参与的决策者\n308: \n309: 核心理念：\n310: ├─ PM Agent是自主智能体（不是人类工具）\n311: ├─ Human参与最小化（只在必要时介入）\n312: ├─ 质量门控判断介入时机\n313: └─ PM Agent主导模式（首问负责制）\n314: ```\n315: \n316: 📖 [研究日志](docs/research/research-log.md) | [框架对比](docs/research/framework-comparison.md)\n317: \n318: ---\n319: \n320: ## 🔄 持续研究\n321: \n322: ### 信息流架构\n323: \n324: **研究问题**: \"人-智能-基础能力\"三层架构中，信息流如何设计？\n325: \n326: **探索方向**:\n327: - Agent First vs Human First 的适用场景\n328: - 信息流性价比分析\n329: - 动态平衡机制\n330: \n331: 📖 [探索研究](docs/research/information-architecture/)\n332: \n333: ---\n334: \n335: ### Token-Based管理 📊\n336: \n337: **研究问题**: Token能否作为Agent工作量度量单位？\n338: \n339: **方法论**:\n340: - Token作为工作量单位\n341: - Velocity（速度）概念\n342: - 预测模型设计\n343: \n344: 📖 [参与探讨](docs/research/token-based/)\n345: \n346: ---\n347: \n348: ## 📖 方法论\n349: \n350: ### 文档分层体系\n351: \n352: ```\n353: Level 0 (必需) ─── <50行  ─── 启动时加载\n354: Level 1 (按需) ─── <100行 ─── 工作时加载  \n355: Level 2 (参考) ─── 不限   ─── 按需查询\n356: ```\n357: \n358: **核心价值**: 最小化Context占用，最大化信息效用\n359: \n360: 📖 [详细说明](docs/methodology/document-hierarchy.md)\n361: \n362: ---\n363: \n364: ### Context最小化\n365: \n366: - **按需披露**: 只加载必要信息\n367: - **索引驱动**: 通过索引快速定位\n368: - **主动清理**: 及时释放无用信息\n369: \n370: 📖 [详细说明](docs/methodology/context-minimization.md)\n371: \n372: ---\n373: \n374: ### 边界隔离\n375: \n376: - **单向依赖**: 避免循环依赖\n377: - **明确归属**: 每个文件有明确责任人\n378: - **代码审查**: 跨边界修改需审批\n379: \n380: 📖 [详细说明](docs/methodology/boundary-isolation.md)\n381: \n382: ---\n383: \n384: ## 🚀 未来方向\n385: \n386: ### 短期（3个月）\n387: - 交互协议标准化\n388: - Message Queue原型\n389: \n390: ### 中期（6个月）\n391: - 半自动化协作流程\n392: - 跨项目验证\n393: \n394: ### 长期（1年）\n395: - 完整通用框架\n396: - 开源生态建设\n397: \n398: 📖 [详细规划](docs/reference/future-directions.md)\n399: \n400: ---\n401: \n402: ## 🤝 参与贡献\n403: \n404: 欢迎：\n405: - 💬 **理论探讨** - 对研究假设的建议\n406: - 🧪 **实验验证** - 在其他场景中验证\n407: - 🐛 **问题发现** - 实践中的问题\n408: - 💡 **创新想法** - 新的研究方向\n409: \n410: **参与方式**: [GitHub Discussions](https://github.com/Sonnet0524/SG-AgentTeam/discussions) | [提交Issue](https://github.com/Sonnet0524/SG-AgentTeam/issues)\n411: \n412: ---\n413: \n414: # 🛠️ 实践篇\n415: \n416: > 本项目(SG-AgentTeam)的Agent Team设计与实现\n417: \n418: ## 🚀 快速开始\n419: \n420: **想复刻这个实践？** 👉 [复刻实践指南](practice/GETTING-STARTED.md)\n421: \n422: ---\n423: \n424: ## 📋 项目概述\n425: \n426: **项目名称**: Knowledge Assistant  \n427: **项目目标**: 个人知识管理助手  \n428: **验证重点**: Agent Team Framework的可行性\n429: \n430: ### 团队配置\n431: \n432: | Agent | 职责 | 模块边界 |\n433: |-------|------|---------|\n434: | **PM** | 项目管理、协调、进度跟踪 | management/ |\n435: | **Data** | 数据模型、解析器、存储层 | data/, parsers/ |\n436: | **Template** | 模板引擎、配置系统 | template/, config/ |\n437: | **Test** | 测试框架、质量保证 | tests/, QA流程 |\n438: | **Research** | 框架研究、方法论提炼 | docs/research/, docs/methodology/ |\n439: \n440: ---\n441: \n442: ## 🏗️ 架构设计\n443: \n444: ### 目录结构\n445: \n446: ```\n447: SG-AgentTeam/\n448: ├── agents/                  # 🤖 框架层Agent\n449: │   └── research/            # Research Agent\n450: ├── docs/                    # 📚 框架文档\n451: │   ├── research/            # 核心研究\n452: │   ├── methodology/         # 方法论\n453: │   └── ...\n454: ├── practice/                # 🛠️ 实践部分\n455: │   ├── agents/              # 🤖 实践层Agent\n456: │   │   ├── pm/\n457: │   │   ├── data/\n458: │   │   ├── template/\n459: │   │   └── test/\n460: │   ├── management/          # 📊 项目管理\n461: │   ├── knowledge-base/      # 🧠 知识库\n462: │   ├── status/              # 📈 状态文档\n463: │   └── ...\n464: └── opencode.json            # ⚙️ Agent配置\n465: ```\n466: \n467: ### 交互机制\n468: \n469: ```\n470: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n471: │                    Human Admin                           │\n472: │                  (决策、监控、干预)                        │\n473: └─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────┘\n474:                       │\n475:         ┌─────────────┴─────────────┐\n476:         │        PM Agent            │\n477:         │    (协调、调度、跟踪)        │\n478:         └─────────────┬─────────────┘\n479:                       │\n480:     ┌─────────┬───────┼───────┬─────────┐\n481:     ▼         ▼       ▼       ▼         ▼\n482:  Data    Template   Test  Research   ...\n483:     │         │       │       │\n484:     └─────────┴───────┴───────┴─────────┘\n485:                       │\n486:               文档化交互（共享上下文）\n487: ```\n488: \n489: ---\n490: \n491: ## 🚀 快速开始\n492: \n493: **详细指南**: [复刻实践指南](practice/GETTING-STARTED.md)\n494: \n495: ### 启动Agent\n496: \n497: ```bash\n498: ./start-pm.sh        # PM Agent - 项目管理\n499: ./start-data.sh      # Data Agent - 数据开发\n500: ./start-template.sh  # Template Agent - 模板开发\n501: ./start-test.sh      # Test Agent - 测试保证\n502: ./start-research.sh  # Research Agent - 框架研究\n503: ```\n504: \n505: ### Agent入口文件\n506: \n507: ```\n508: agents/research/CATCH_UP.md      # Research Agent (框架层)\n509: practice/agents/pm/CATCH_UP.md       # PM Agent (实践层)\n510: practice/agents/data/CATCH_UP.md     # Data Agent\n511: practice/agents/template/CATCH_UP.md # Template Agent\n512: practice/agents/test/CATCH_UP.md     # Test Agent\n513: ```\n514: \n515: ---\n516: \n517: ## 📊 实践成果\n518: \n519: ### 验证结论\n520: \n521: ✅ **文档化交互可行且有效**  \n522: ✅ **分层文档体系显著降低Context消耗**  \n523: ✅ **明确的模块边界消除协作冲突**  \n524: ⚠️ **Token-Based管理需进一步优化**\n525: \n526: ### 详细报告\n527: \n528: 📖 [实践验证报告](docs/practice/SG-AgentTeam/)  \n529: 📖 [经验教训总结](docs/practice/lessons-learned/)\n530: \n531: ---\n532: \n533: ## 📚 框架文档导航\n534: \n535: ### 快速入门\n536: - 🎓 [研究概览](docs/) - 了解研究全貌\n537: - 🔬 [Agent交互模式](docs/research/agent-interaction/) - 核心研究\n538: \n539: ### 深入了解\n540: - 📖 [方法论](docs/methodology/) - 文档分层、Context最小化等\n541: - 📊 [经验教训](docs/practice/lessons-learned/) - 实践总结\n542: - 🔍 [对比分析](docs/reference/comparison.md) - 与其他方法对比\n543: \n544: ---\n545: \n546: ## 📖 引用\n547: \n548: ```bibtex\n549: @misc{agent-team-framework-2026,\n550:   title={Agent Team Framework: A Document-based Agent Interaction Model},\n551:   author={Agent Team},\n552:   year={2026},\n553:   url={https://github.com/Sonnet0524/SG-AgentTeam}\n554: }\n555: ```\n556: \n557: ---\n558: \n559: ## 📜 许可协议\n560: \n561: ### 代码部分\n562: \n563: 本项目代码采用 **GNU Affero General Public License v3.0 (AGPL v3.0)** 协议开源。\n564: \n565: [![License: AGPL v3](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-AGPL%20v3-blue.svg)](https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0)\n566: \n567: **关键要求**：\n568: - ✅ 自由使用、修改和分发\n569: - ✅ 任何修改版本必须以AGPL开源\n570: - ✅ 网络服务使用也必须开源（AGPL特有）\n571: - ✅ 必须保留版权声明\n572: \n573: **商业使用**：如需商业使用，请联系获取商业许可。\n574: \n575: 📄 [查看完整协议](LICENSE)\n576: \n577: ---\n578: \n579: ### 知识内容\n580: \n581: 本项目的文档、知识库等知识内容采用 **CC BY-NC-SA 4.0** 协议。\n582: \n583: **关键要求**：\n584: - ✅ 必须署名\n585: - ❌ 禁止商业使用\n586: - ✅ 相同方式共享\n587: \n588: **商业使用**：如需商业使用，请联系获取商业许可。\n589: \n590: 📄 [查看完整协议](KNOWLEDGE_LICENSE)\n591: \n592: ---\n593: \n594: ## 🏷️ 版权声明\n595: \n596: Copyright © 2026 Agent Team. All rights reserved.\n597: \n598: 本项目包括：\n599: - 代码（AGPL v3.0）：允许开源使用，禁止闭源商业使用\n600: - 知识（CC BY-NC-SA 4.0）：允许非商业使用，禁止商业使用\n601: \n602: **商业合作**：通过 [GitHub Issues](https://github.com/Sonnet0524/SG-AgentTeam/issues) 联系\n\n(End of file - total 602 lines)\n</content>","title":"README.md","metadata":{"preview":"# Agent Team Framework\n\n> 🤝 基于文档的AI Agent协作框架\n\n**版本**: v1.1 | **状态**: 实践验证中 | **更新**: 2026-03-07\n\n---\n\n## 💡 核心理念\n\n让多个AI Agent像人类团队一样**高效、可靠地协作**——通过**文档化交互**实现异步、可追溯、可自动化的协作模式。\n\n## 📚 研究框架\n\n本项目使用 **[SEARCH-R Framework](https://github.com/Sonnet0524/SEARCH-R)** 进行系统性研究。\n\nSEARCH-R是一个通用的研究型Agent框架，提供：\n- 🔍 **SEARCH-R方法论** - 完整的研究循环\n- 🤖 **Research Agent模板** - 可复用的研究Agent\n- 📄 **标准文档模板** - 研究文档的标准格式","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1772871941222,"end":1772871941224}}}}
