{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772871965500,"sessionID":"ses_3389967ebffeq10PXnV18VW536","part":{"id":"prt_cc7675b34001wqmfYTNUCyMEq3","sessionID":"ses_3389967ebffeq10PXnV18VW536","messageID":"msg_cc767444e0013XpjJcURbe294J","type":"tool","callID":"call_197e67843e2049ec8b5079dd","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/sonnet/opencode/SG-AgentTeam/skills/knowledge-assistant/SKILL.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/sonnet/opencode/SG-AgentTeam/skills/knowledge-assistant/SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: # Knowledge Assistant - Skill Definition\n2: \n3: > 🎯 A semantic knowledge management skill for intelligent document indexing and retrieval\n4: \n5: **Version**: v1.1  \n6: **Last Updated**: 2026-03-07  \n7: **Author**: Integration Team  \n8: **Status**: Production Ready\n9: \n10: ---\n11: \n12: ## 📖 Overview\n13: \n14: **Knowledge Assistant** is a specialized skill that provides semantic indexing, intelligent search, knowledge extraction, and multi-source integration capabilities. It transforms how you interact with your document collections by understanding the semantic meaning of your queries.\n15: \n16: ### Core Capabilities\n17: \n18: - 🔨 **Build Knowledge Base** - Create semantic indexes from document collections\n19: - 🔍 **Semantic Search** - Find documents by meaning, not just keywords\n20: - 📊 **Knowledge Extraction** - Extract keywords and generate summaries\n21: - 📧 **Multi-Source Integration** - Search across documents, emails, and more\n22: \n23: ### Design Philosophy\n24: \n25: ```\n26: opencode (Master Agent)\n27:   ├── File operations (built-in)\n28:   ├── Natural language understanding (built-in)\n29:   ├── Intent recognition (built-in)\n30:   └── Calls Knowledge Assistant tools\n31:       ↓\n32: Knowledge Assistant (Tool Library)\n33:   ├── build_semantic_index() → IndexResult\n34:   ├── semantic_search() → [SearchResult]\n35:   ├── extract_keywords() → [Keyword]\n36:   ├── generate_summary() → Summary\n37:   └── EmailConnector → EmailData\n38: ```\n39: \n40: **Key Principle**: Knowledge Assistant provides algorithms and returns structured data. opencode handles file operations, user interaction, and result presentation.\n41: \n42: ---\n43: \n44: ## 🎯 Trigger Patterns\n45: \n46: Knowledge Assistant is triggered by natural language phrases indicating knowledge management intents.\n47: \n48: ### Intent Categories\n49: \n50: #### 1. Build Knowledge Base\n51: \n52: **Trigger Phrases**:\n53: ```\n54: - \"build knowledge base from {directory}\"\n55: - \"create index for {path}\"\n56: - \"index my documents in {folder}\"\n57: - \"add {directory} to knowledge base\"\n58: - \"构建知识库从 {目录}\"\n59: - \"为 {路径} 创建索引\"\n60: ```\n61: \n62: **Extracted Parameters**:\n63: - `directory`: Path to document collection (required)\n64: - `index_name`: Custom index name (optional, default: \".ka-index\")\n65: - `recursive`: Include subdirectories (optional, default: true)\n66: \n67: **Example**:\n68: ```\n69: User: \"build knowledge base from ./notes\"\n70: opencode: \n71:   1. Scans ./notes directory\n72:   2. Reads all document files\n73:   3. Calls build_semantic_index(documents)\n74:   4. Reports: \"Indexed 156 documents, created 489 chunks\"\n75: ```\n76: \n77: ---\n78: \n79: #### 2. Search Documents\n80: \n81: **Trigger Phrases**:\n82: ```\n83: - \"search for {query}\"\n84: - \"find documents about {topic}\"\n85: - \"查找关于 {主题} 的文档\"\n86: - \"搜索 {关键词}\"\n87: - \"what documents mention {term}\"\n88: ```\n89: \n90: **Extracted Parameters**:\n91: - `query`: Search query text (required)\n92: - `top_k`: Number of results (optional, default: 5)\n93: - `filters`: Metadata filters (optional)\n94: - `threshold`: Similarity threshold (optional)\n95: \n96: **Example**:\n97: ```\n98: User: \"find documents about Python async programming\"\n99: opencode:\n100:   1. Recognizes search intent\n101:   2. Calls semantic_search(\"Python async programming\")\n102:   3. Reads top results from disk\n103:   4. Displays: \"Found 5 relevant documents...\"\n104: ```\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: #### 3. Extract Knowledge\n109: \n110: **Trigger Phrases**:\n111: ```\n112: - \"extract keywords from {document}\"\n113: - \"summarize {document}\"\n114: - \"what are the key points in {path}\"\n115: - \"从 {文档} 提取关键词\"\n116: - \"总结 {文档}\"\n117: ```\n118: \n119: **Extracted Parameters**:\n120: - `document`: Path to document or content (required)\n121: - `method`: Extraction method (optional: \"tfidf\", \"textrank\")\n122: - `top_n`: Number of keywords (optional, default: 10)\n123: \n124: **Example**:\n125: ```\n126: User: \"extract keywords from ./notes/python.md\"\n127: opencode:\n128:   1. Reads ./notes/python.md\n129:   2. Calls extract_keywords(content)\n130:   3. Displays: \"Keywords: Python, async, concurrent, ...\"\n131: ```\n132: \n133: ---\n134: \n135: #### 4. Multi-Source Search\n136: \n137: **Trigger Phrases**:\n138: ```\n139: - \"search emails for {query}\"\n140: - \"find in all sources: {query}\"\n141: - \"search my emails and documents for {topic}\"\n142: - \"搜索邮件中的 {关键词}\"\n143: ```\n144: \n145: **Extracted Parameters**:\n146: - `query`: Search query (required)\n147: - `sources`: List of sources (optional: [\"documents\", \"emails\"])\n148: - `email_folder`: Email folder to search (optional)\n149: \n150: **Example**:\n151: ```\n152: User: \"search emails for project budget\"\n153: opencode:\n154:   1. Recognizes email search intent\n155:   2. Connects to EmailConnector\n156:   3. Searches emails\n157:   4. Displays: \"Found 3 emails about project budget...\"\n158: ```\n159: \n160: ---\n161: \n162: ## 🛠️ Tool Functions\n163: \n164: ### 1. build_semantic_index\n165: \n166: **Purpose**: Create a semantic vector index from a document collection.\n167: \n168: **API**:\n169: ```python\n170: from scripts.tools.indexing import build_semantic_index\n171: \n172: result = build_semantic_index(\n173:     documents: List[Dict],      # Document list\n174:     index_path: str = \".ka-index\",  # Index directory\n175:     chunk_size: int = 256,      # Chunk size in characters\n176:     chunk_overlap: int = 50,    # Overlap between chunks\n177:     batch_size: int = 8,        # Batch size for encoding\n178:     model_name: str = \"BAAI/bge-small-zh-v1.5\",  # Embedding model\n179:     show_progress: bool = False  # Show progress bar\n180: ) -> Dict\n181: ```\n182: \n183: **Input Format**:\n184: ```python\n185: documents = [\n186:     {\n187:         'content': 'Document text content...',\n188:         'metadata': {\n189:             'path': './notes/python.md',\n190:             'title': 'Python Guide',\n191:             'date': '2024-01-15',\n192:             # ... custom metadata\n193:         }\n194:     },\n195:     # ... more documents\n196: ]\n197: ```\n198: \n199: **Output Format**:\n200: ```python\n201: {\n202:     'success': True,\n203:     'total_docs': 156,\n204:     'total_chunks': 489,\n205:     'index_size': '23.5 MB',\n206:     'build_time': '12.3s',\n207:     'model': 'BAAI/bge-small-zh-v1.5',\n208:     'dimension': 512,\n209:     'index_path': '.ka-index'\n210: }\n211: ```\n212: \n213: **opencode Usage**:\n214: ```python\n215: # opencode provides documents (scans files)\n216: documents = []  # opencode fills this\n217: for file_path in scan_directory(\"./notes\"):\n218:     content = read_file(file_path)\n219:     documents.append({\n220:         'content': content,\n221:         'metadata': {'path': file_path}\n222:     })\n223: \n224: # opencode calls knowledge-assistant tool\n225: result = build_semantic_index(documents)\n226: \n227: # opencode presents results\n228: print(f\"Indexed {result['total_docs']} documents\")\n229: ```\n230: \n231: **Performance**:\n232: - 100 docs: ~1s\n233: - 1000 docs: ~15s\n234: - 2000 docs: <40s (target)\n235: \n236: ---\n237: \n238: ### 2. semantic_search\n239: \n240: **Purpose**: Perform semantic search on an indexed collection.\n241: \n242: **API**:\n243: ```python\n244: from scripts.tools.search import semantic_search\n245: \n246: results = semantic_search(\n247:     query: str,                 # Search query\n248:     index_path: str = \".ka-index\",  # Index directory\n249:     top_k: int = 5,             # Max results\n250:     filters: Optional[Dict] = None,  # Metadata filters\n251:     threshold: Optional[float] = None,  # Similarity threshold\n252:     model_name: str = \"BAAI/bge-small-zh-v1.5\"  # Model name\n253: ) -> List[Dict]\n254: ```\n255: \n256: **Input Format**:\n257: ```python\n258: # Natural language query\n259: query = \"Python异步编程最佳实践\"\n260: \n261: # Optional filters\n262: filters = {\n263:     'category': 'programming',\n264:     'date_from': '2024-01-01'\n265: }\n266: ```\n267: \n268: **Output Format**:\n269: ```python\n270: [\n271:     {\n272:         'rank': 1,\n273:         'similarity': 0.89,\n274:         'snippet': 'Python async programming allows...',\n275:         'metadata': {\n276:             'path': './notes/python.md',\n277:             'title': 'Python Guide',\n278:             # ... other metadata\n279:         },\n280:         'index': 42  # Chunk index\n281:     },\n282:     # ... more results\n283: ]\n284: ```\n285: \n286: **opencode Usage**:\n287: ```python\n288: # opencode understands user intent\n289: query = \"Python异步编程\"\n290: \n291: # opencode calls knowledge-assistant tool\n292: results = semantic_search(query, top_k=5)\n293: \n294: # opencode reads and displays documents\n295: for result in results:\n296:     doc_path = result['metadata']['path']\n297:     content = read_file(doc_path)\n298:     display_result(\n299:         title=result['metadata']['title'],\n300:         snippet=result['snippet'],\n301:         similarity=result['similarity'],\n302:         full_content=content\n303:     )\n304: ```\n305: \n306: **Performance**:\n307: - Query latency: <150ms\n308: - Accuracy: >85% for relevant queries\n309: \n310: ---\n311: \n312: ### 3. extract_keywords\n313: \n314: **Purpose**: Extract keywords from text content.\n315: \n316: **API**:\n317: ```python\n318: from scripts.tools.extraction import extract_keywords\n319: \n320: keywords = extract_keywords(\n321:     content: str,               # Text content\n322:     method: str = \"tfidf\",      # Method: \"tfidf\" or \"textrank\"\n323:     top_n: int = 10             # Number of keywords\n324: ) -> List[Dict]\n325: ```\n326: \n327: **Output Format**:\n328: ```python\n329: [\n330:     {\n331:         'keyword': 'Python',\n332:         'score': 0.85,\n333:         'frequency': 15\n334:     },\n335:     {\n336:         'keyword': '异步编程',\n337:         'score': 0.78,\n338:         'frequency': 12\n339:     },\n340:     # ... more keywords\n341: ]\n342: ```\n343: \n344: **opencode Usage**:\n345: ```python\n346: # opencode reads document\n347: content = read_file(\"./notes/python.md\")\n348: \n349: # opencode calls knowledge-assistant tool\n350: keywords = extract_keywords(content, method=\"textrank\")\n351: \n352: # opencode displays keywords\n353: for kw in keywords:\n354:     print(f\"- {kw['keyword']} (score: {kw['score']:.2f})\")\n355: ```\n356: \n357: ---\n358: \n359: ### 4. generate_summary\n360: \n361: **Purpose**: Generate a summary from text content.\n362: \n363: **API**:\n364: ```python\n365: from scripts.tools.extraction import generate_summary\n366: \n367: summary = generate_summary(\n368:     content: str,               # Text content\n369:     max_length: int = 200,      # Max characters\n370:     method: str = \"extractive\"  # Method: \"extractive\"\n371: ) -> Dict\n372: ```\n373: \n374: **Output Format**:\n375: ```python\n376: {\n377:     'summary': 'Python是一种广泛使用的编程语言，支持异步编程...',\n378:     'length': 150,\n379:     'compression_ratio': 0.15,  # Original length / summary length\n380:     'key_sentences': [\n381:         'Python是一种广泛使用的编程语言',\n382:         '支持异步编程特性',\n383:         # ...\n384:     ]\n385: }\n386: ```\n387: \n388: **opencode Usage**:\n389: ```python\n390: # opencode reads document\n391: content = read_file(\"./notes/python.md\")\n392: \n393: # opencode calls knowledge-assistant tool\n394: result = generate_summary(content, max_length=200)\n395: \n396: # opencode displays summary\n397: print(f\"Summary: {result['summary']}\")\n398: ```\n399: \n400: ---\n401: \n402: ### 5. EmailConnector\n403: \n404: **Purpose**: Connect to email servers and search emails.\n405: \n406: **API**:\n407: ```python\n408: from scripts.connectors.email import EmailConnector, EmailConfig\n409: \n410: # Configure connection\n411: config = EmailConfig(\n412:     server=\"imap.gmail.com\",\n413:     port=993,\n414:     username=\"user@gmail.com\",\n415:     password=\"app_password\",\n416:     use_ssl=True\n417: )\n418: \n419: # Create connector\n420: connector = EmailConnector(config=config)\n421: \n422: # Connect\n423: if connector.connect():\n424:     # Search emails\n425:     results = connector.search(\n426:         query=\"project budget\",\n427:         limit=10,\n428:         folders=[\"INBOX\"],\n429:         filters={\n430:             'date_from': '2024-01-01',\n431:             'unread_only': False\n432:         }\n433:     )\n434:     \n435:     # Get full email\n436:     email = connector.get_by_id(\"msg_123\")\n437:     \n438:     # Disconnect\n439:     connector.disconnect()\n440: ```\n441: \n442: **Search Output Format**:\n443: ```python\n444: [\n445:     {\n446:         'id': '123',\n447:         'title': 'Budget Report Q1',\n448:         'snippet': 'Please find attached the Q1 budget...',\n449:         'source': 'email',\n450:         'metadata': {\n451:             'sender': 'boss@company.com',\n452:             'sender_name': 'John Doe',\n453:             'folder': 'INBOX',\n454:             'is_read': True,\n455:             'has_attachments': True,\n456:             'flags': ['seen']\n457:         },\n458:         'timestamp': datetime(2024, 1, 15, 10, 30)\n459:     },\n460:     # ... more results\n461: ]\n462: ```\n463: \n464: **opencode Usage**:\n465: ```python\n466: # opencode recognizes email search intent\n467: query = \"project budget\"\n468: \n469: # opencode uses EmailConnector\n470: config = EmailConfig(\n471:     server=get_config('email.server'),\n472:     username=get_config('email.username'),\n473:     password=get_config('email.password')\n474: )\n475: \n476: with EmailConnector(config) as connector:\n477:     results = connector.search(query)\n478:     \n479:     # opencode displays results\n480:     for result in results:\n481:         display_email_result(\n482:             subject=result['title'],\n483:             sender=result['metadata']['sender'],\n484:             date=result['timestamp'],\n485:             snippet=result['snippet']\n486:         )\n487: ```\n488: \n489: ---\n490: \n491: ## 📋 Complete Usage Examples\n492: \n493: ### Example 1: Build and Search Knowledge Base\n494: \n495: **User Request**:\n496: ```\n497: \"Build a knowledge base from my notes folder and search for Python async programming\"\n498: ```\n499: \n500: **opencode Workflow**:\n501: ```python\n502: # Step 1: Scan directory\n503: documents = []\n504: for file_path in scan_directory(\"./notes\", recursive=True):\n505:     if file_path.endswith(('.md', '.txt', '.pdf')):\n506:         content = read_file(file_path)\n507:         metadata = extract_metadata(file_path)\n508:         documents.append({\n509:             'content': content,\n510:             'metadata': metadata\n511:         })\n512: \n513: # Step 2: Build index\n514: result = build_semantic_index(documents)\n515: print(f\"✓ Indexed {result['total_docs']} documents\")\n516: print(f\"✓ Created {result['total_chunks']} chunks in {result['build_time']}\")\n517: \n518: # Step 3: Search\n519: results = semantic_search(\"Python async programming\", top_k=5)\n520: \n521: # Step 4: Display results\n522: for i, result in enumerate(results, 1):\n523:     print(f\"\\n{i}. {result['metadata']['title']}\")\n524:     print(f\"   Similarity: {result['similarity']:.2f}\")\n525:     print(f\"   Path: {result['metadata']['path']}\")\n526:     print(f\"   Snippet: {result['snippet'][:100]}...\")\n527: ```\n528: \n529: **Output**:\n530: ```\n531: ✓ Indexed 156 documents\n532: ✓ Created 489 chunks in 12.3s\n533: \n534: Found 5 relevant documents:\n535: \n536: 1. Python异步编程指南\n537:    Similarity: 0.89\n538:    Path: ./notes/python/async.md\n539:    Snippet: Python async programming allows you to write concurrent code using the async/await syntax...\n540: \n541: 2. 并发编程最佳实践\n542:    Similarity: 0.85\n543:    Path: ./notes/python/concurrency.md\n544:    Snippet: When working with async programming in Python, consider the following best practices...\n545: ...\n546: ```\n547: \n548: ---\n549: \n550: ### Example 2: Extract Knowledge from Document\n551: \n552: **User Request**:\n553: ```\n554: \"Extract keywords and summarize the document at ./notes/python.md\"\n555: ```\n556: \n557: **opencode Workflow**:\n558: ```python\n559: # Step 1: Read document\n560: content = read_file(\"./notes/python.md\")\n561: \n562: # Step 2: Extract keywords\n563: keywords = extract_keywords(content, method=\"textrank\", top_n=10)\n564: \n565: # Step 3: Generate summary\n566: summary = generate_summary(content, max_length=200)\n567: \n568: # Step 4: Display results\n569: print(\"📄 Document: python.md\\n\")\n570: print(\"🔑 Keywords:\")\n571: for kw in keywords[:5]:\n572:     print(f\"  - {kw['keyword']} (score: {kw['score']:.2f})\")\n573: \n574: print(\"\\n📝 Summary:\")\n575: print(summary['summary'])\n576: print(f\"\\nCompression ratio: {summary['compression_ratio']:.2f}\")\n577: ```\n578: \n579: **Output**:\n580: ```\n581: 📄 Document: python.md\n582: \n583: 🔑 Keywords:\n584:   - Python (score: 0.89)\n585:   - 异步编程 (score: 0.85)\n586:   - 并发 (score: 0.78)\n587:   - async/await (score: 0.75)\n588:   - 性能优化 (score: 0.72)\n589: \n590: 📝 Summary:\n591: Python是一种广泛使用的编程语言，支持异步编程特性。通过async/await语法，可以编写高效的并发代码。异步编程适用于I/O密集型任务，能显著提升程序性能。\n592: \n593: Compression ratio: 0.15\n594: ```\n595: \n596: ---\n597: \n598: ### Example 3: Multi-Source Search\n599: \n600: **User Request**:\n601: ```\n602: \"Search for 'budget meeting' in my emails and documents\"\n603: ```\n604: \n605: **opencode Workflow**:\n606: ```python\n607: # Step 1: Search documents\n608: doc_results = semantic_search(\"budget meeting\", top_k=3)\n609: \n610: # Step 2: Search emails\n611: email_config = EmailConfig(\n612:     server=get_config('email.server'),\n613:     username=get_config('email.username'),\n614:     password=get_config('email.password')\n615: )\n616: \n617: email_results = []\n618: with EmailConnector(email_config) as connector:\n619:     email_results = connector.search(\"budget meeting\", limit=3)\n620: \n621: # Step 3: Merge and rank results\n622: all_results = merge_results(doc_results, email_results)\n623: \n624: # Step 4: Display unified results\n625: print(f\"Found {len(all_results)} results:\\n\")\n626: \n627: for i, result in enumerate(all_results, 1):\n628:     if result['source'] == 'document':\n629:         print(f\"{i}. [Document] {result['metadata']['title']}\")\n630:         print(f\"   Path: {result['metadata']['path']}\")\n631:     else:\n632:         print(f\"{i}. [Email] {result['title']}\")\n633:         print(f\"   From: {result['metadata']['sender']}\")\n634:     print(f\"   Snippet: {result['snippet'][:80]}...\\n\")\n635: ```\n636: \n637: **Output**:\n638: ```\n639: Found 6 results:\n640: \n641: 1. [Email] Budget Meeting Notes - Q1 Review\n642:    From: boss@company.com\n643:    Snippet: Attached are the notes from today's budget meeting. We discussed...\n644: \n645: 2. [Document] Budget Planning 2024\n646:    Path: ./notes/budget/planning.md\n647:    Snippet: Budget meeting scheduled for next week. Key topics include...\n648: \n649: 3. [Email] Re: Budget Meeting Tomorrow\n650:    From: colleague@company.com\n651:    Snippet: I'll prepare the budget meeting materials as discussed...\n652: ...\n653: ```\n654: \n655: ---\n656: \n657: ## 🔧 Error Handling\n658: \n659: ### Common Errors and Solutions\n660: \n661: #### 1. Index Not Found\n662: \n663: **Error**:\n664: ```\n665: FileNotFoundError: Index not found at .ka-index\n666: ```\n667: \n668: **opencode Response**:\n669: ```\n670: \"I couldn't find a knowledge base index. Would you like me to build one? \n671: Just tell me which directory to index, for example: \n672: 'Build knowledge base from ./notes'\"\n673: ```\n674: \n675: #### 2. Email Not Configured\n676: \n677: **Error**:\n678: ```\n679: ValueError: Email server configuration missing\n680: ```\n681: \n682: **opencode Response**:\n683: ```\n684: \"Email search requires configuration. Would you like to set up email access?\n685: I'll need:\n686: - IMAP server (e.g., imap.gmail.com)\n687: - Email address\n688: - Password or app password\n689: \n690: You can provide these securely, or skip email search for now.\"\n691: ```\n692: \n693: #### 3. Model Loading Failed\n694: \n695: **Error**:\n696: ```\n697: RuntimeError: Failed to load embedding model\n698: ```\n699: \n700: **opencode Response**:\n701: ```\n702: \"The embedding model couldn't be loaded. This might be the first time \n703: using Knowledge Assistant. The model will be downloaded automatically \n704: (~130MB). Please ensure you have internet connection and try again.\"\n705: ```\n706: \n707: ---\n708: \n709: ## 🎓 Best Practices\n710: \n711: ### For opencode Users\n712: \n713: 1. **Build Index Before Searching**\n714:    ```\n715:    # Good\n716:    User: \"Build index from ./notes\"\n717:    User: \"Search for Python async\"\n718:    \n719:    # Bad\n720:    User: \"Search for Python async\"  # No index exists\n721:    ```\n722: \n723: 2. **Use Natural Language**\n724:    ```\n725:    # Good\n726:    \"Find documents about machine learning\"\n727:    \"What do I have about Python async programming?\"\n728:    \n729:    # Also good\n730:    \"搜索关于机器学习的文档\"\n731:    \n732:    # Less natural\n733:    \"semantic_search machine learning\"  # Too technical\n734:    ```\n735: \n736: 3. **Provide Context**\n737:    ```\n738:    # Good\n739:    \"Search my notes folder for Python async programming\"\n740:    \n741:    # Less specific\n742:    \"Search for Python\"  # Might return too many results\n743:    ```\n744: \n745: 4. **Use Filters When Appropriate**\n746:    ```\n747:    \"Find documents about budget from January 2024\"\n748:    \"Search unread emails for project updates\"\n749:    ```\n750: \n751: ### For Developers\n752: \n753: 1. **Separation of Concerns**\n754:    - Knowledge Assistant: Provides algorithms and returns structured data\n755:    - opencode: Handles file I/O, user interaction, presentation\n756: \n757: 2. **Structured Data Exchange**\n758:    ```python\n759:    # Good - structured data\n760:    result = build_semantic_index(documents)\n761:    return {\n762:        'success': True,\n763:        'total_docs': 156,\n764:        'total_chunks': 489\n765:    }\n766:    \n767:    # Bad - mixed concerns\n768:    result = build_semantic_index(documents)\n769:    print(f\"Indexed {result['total_docs']} documents\")  # Don't print!\n770:    return result\n771:    ```\n772: \n773: 3. **Error Propagation**\n774:    ```python\n775:    # Good - let opencode handle errors\n776:    try:\n777:        result = semantic_search(query)\n778:        return result\n779:    except FileNotFoundError:\n780:        raise  # Let opencode catch and explain to user\n781:    \n782:    # Bad - handle errors internally\n783:    try:\n784:        result = semantic_search(query)\n785:    except FileNotFoundError:\n786:        print(\"Index not found\")  # Don't handle presentation!\n787:        return None\n788:    ```\n789: \n790: ---\n791: \n792: ## 🔮 Future Enhancements\n793: \n794: ### Planned Features (v1.2+)\n795: \n796: - **Incremental Indexing**: Update index without rebuilding\n797: - **Multi-Modal Support**: Images, PDFs, code files\n798: - **Federated Search**: Search across multiple knowledge bases\n799: - **Caching Layer**: Faster repeated searches\n800: - **Export/Import**: Share knowledge bases\n801: \n802: ### Experimental Features\n803: \n804: - **RAG Integration**: Retrieval-augmented generation\n805: - **Semantic Clustering**: Auto-categorize documents\n806: - **Entity Extraction**: Named entity recognition\n807: - **Graph Relationships**: Knowledge graph construction\n808: \n809: ---\n810: \n811: ## 📚 References\n812: \n813: ### Technical Documentation\n814: \n815: - [Technical Design v1.1](../../docs/technical-design-v1.1.md)\n816: - [Email Connector Guide](../../docs/email-connector-guide.md)\n817: - [API Reference](../../docs/api-reference.md)\n818: \n819: ### Research\n820: \n821: - [Agent Interaction Pattern](../../docs/research/agent-interaction/)\n822: - [Agent Society Architecture](../../docs/research/agent-society/)\n823: \n824: ---\n825: \n826: ## 📝 Version History\n827: \n828: | Version | Date | Changes |\n829: |---------|------|---------|\n830: | v1.1 | 2026-03-07 | Initial skill definition with core tools |\n831: | v1.0 | 2026-02-15 | Project conception |\n832: \n833: ---\n834: \n835: **Maintained by**: Integration Team  \n836: **Contact**: Create an issue at GitHub repository  \n837: **License**: MIT\n\n(End of file - total 837 lines)\n</content>","title":"skills/knowledge-assistant/SKILL.md","metadata":{"preview":"# Knowledge Assistant - Skill Definition\n\n> 🎯 A semantic knowledge management skill for intelligent document indexing and retrieval\n\n**Version**: v1.1  \n**Last Updated**: 2026-03-07  \n**Author**: Integration Team  \n**Status**: Production Ready\n\n---\n\n## 📖 Overview\n\n**Knowledge Assistant** is a specialized skill that provides semantic indexing, intelligent search, knowledge extraction, and multi-source integration capabilities. It transforms how you interact with your document collections by understanding the semantic meaning of your queries.\n\n### Core Capabilities\n\n- 🔨 **Build Knowledge Base** - Create semantic indexes from document collections\n- 🔍 **Semantic Search** - Find documents by meaning, not just keywords\n- 📊 **Knowledge Extraction** - Extract keywords and generate summaries","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1772871965493,"end":1772871965495}}}}
