{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772871970898,"sessionID":"ses_3389967ebffeq10PXnV18VW536","part":{"id":"prt_cc767704d001IY5tJt63bYlzqB","sessionID":"ses_3389967ebffeq10PXnV18VW536","messageID":"msg_cc7675e4a001O3azbWUU68PSJe","type":"tool","callID":"call_5761a2d1864740399294025f","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/sonnet/opencode/SG-AgentTeam/AGENT.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/sonnet/opencode/SG-AgentTeam/AGENT.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: # Knowledge Assistant Agent Configuration\n2: \n3: > 🤖 Agent configuration for opencode integration\n4: \n5: **Version**: v1.1  \n6: **Last Updated**: 2026-03-07  \n7: **Author**: Integration Team  \n8: **Status**: Production Ready\n9: \n10: ---\n11: \n12: ## 📖 Overview\n13: \n14: **Knowledge Assistant Agent** is a specialized agent that provides intelligent knowledge management capabilities to opencode. It serves as a bridge between user intents and the Knowledge Assistant tool library.\n15: \n16: ### Agent Identity\n17: \n18: - **Name**: Knowledge Assistant\n19: - **Type**: Specialized Tool Agent\n20: - **Role**: Knowledge Management Specialist\n21: - **Capabilities**: Semantic indexing, intelligent search, knowledge extraction, multi-source integration\n22: \n23: ### Relationship with opencode\n24: \n25: ```\n26: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n27: │              opencode (Master Agent)             │\n28: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n29: │  │  User Interaction                          │ │\n30: │  │  - Natural language understanding         │ │\n31: │  │  - Intent recognition                     │ │\n32: │  │  - File operations (scan, read, write)    │ │\n33: │  │  - Result presentation                    │ │\n34: │  └────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n35: │                     ↓ Calls                     │\n36: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n37: │  │    Knowledge Assistant Agent               │ │\n38: │  │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────┐ │ │\n39: │  │  │  Intent → Tool Mapping               │ │ │\n40: │  │  │  - build_knowledge_base              │ │ │\n41: │  │  │  - search_documents                  │ │ │\n42: │  │  │  - extract_knowledge                 │ │ │\n43: │  │  │  - multi_source_search               │ │ │\n44: │  │  └──────────────────────────────────────┘ │ │\n45: │  │                   ↓ Invokes                │ │\n46: │  │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────┐ │ │\n47: │  │  │    Knowledge Assistant Tools         │ │ │\n48: │  │  │  - build_semantic_index()            │ │ │\n49: │  │  │  - semantic_search()                 │ │ │\n50: │  │  │  - extract_keywords()                │ │ │\n51: │  │  │  - generate_summary()                │ │ │\n52: │  │  │  - EmailConnector                    │ │ │\n53: │  │  └──────────────────────────────────────┘ │ │\n54: │  └────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n55: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n56: ```\n57: \n58: **Key Principle**: opencode delegates algorithmic tasks to Knowledge Assistant, which returns structured data. opencode then handles presentation and user interaction.\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ## 🎯 Core Capabilities\n63: \n64: ### 1. Knowledge Base Management\n65: \n66: **Description**: Build and maintain semantic indexes of document collections.\n67: \n68: **When Used**: User wants to create or update a knowledge base.\n69: \n70: **Tools Called**: `build_semantic_index()`\n71: \n72: **Workflow**:\n73: 1. opencode scans directory for documents\n74: 2. opencode reads document contents\n75: 3. Knowledge Assistant builds semantic index\n76: 4. opencode reports results to user\n77: \n78: **Example**:\n79: ```python\n80: # User: \"Build knowledge base from ./notes\"\n81: \n82: # opencode actions:\n83: documents = []\n84: for path in scan_directory(\"./notes\"):\n85:     content = read_file(path)\n86:     documents.append({'content': content, 'metadata': {'path': path}})\n87: \n88: # Knowledge Assistant tool call:\n89: result = build_semantic_index(documents, index_path=\".ka-index\")\n90: \n91: # opencode response:\n92: display(f\"✓ Indexed {result['total_docs']} documents in {result['build_time']}\")\n93: ```\n94: \n95: ---\n96: \n97: ### 2. Semantic Search\n98: \n99: **Description**: Search documents using natural language queries with semantic understanding.\n100: \n101: **When Used**: User wants to find relevant documents.\n102: \n103: **Tools Called**: `semantic_search()`\n104: \n105: **Workflow**:\n106: 1. opencode understands user's search intent\n107: 2. Knowledge Assistant performs semantic search\n108: 3. opencode reads and displays matching documents\n109: \n110: **Example**:\n111: ```python\n112: # User: \"Find documents about Python async programming\"\n113: \n114: # Knowledge Assistant tool call:\n115: results = semantic_search(\"Python async programming\", top_k=5)\n116: \n117: # opencode actions:\n118: for result in results:\n119:     doc_path = result['metadata']['path']\n120:     content = read_file(doc_path)\n121:     display_result(\n122:         title=result['metadata'].get('title', doc_path),\n123:         snippet=result['snippet'],\n124:         similarity=result['similarity'],\n125:         full_content=content\n126:     )\n127: ```\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ### 3. Knowledge Extraction\n132: \n133: **Description**: Extract keywords and generate summaries from documents.\n134: \n135: **When Used**: User wants to understand document content quickly.\n136: \n137: **Tools Called**: `extract_keywords()`, `generate_summary()`\n138: \n139: **Workflow**:\n140: 1. opencode reads document content\n141: 2. Knowledge Assistant extracts keywords/summary\n142: 3. opencode presents extracted knowledge\n143: \n144: **Example**:\n145: ```python\n146: # User: \"Extract keywords from ./notes/python.md\"\n147: \n148: # opencode action:\n149: content = read_file(\"./notes/python.md\")\n150: \n151: # Knowledge Assistant tool call:\n152: keywords = extract_keywords(content, method=\"textrank\", top_n=10)\n153: \n154: # opencode response:\n155: display_keywords(keywords)\n156: ```\n157: \n158: ---\n159: \n160: ### 4. Multi-Source Integration\n161: \n162: **Description**: Search across multiple data sources (documents, emails, etc.).\n163: \n164: **When Used**: User wants to search emails or multiple sources.\n165: \n166: **Tools Called**: `EmailConnector`, `semantic_search()`\n167: \n168: **Workflow**:\n169: 1. opencode recognizes multi-source intent\n170: 2. Knowledge Assistant searches each source\n171: 3. opencode merges and presents unified results\n172: \n173: **Example**:\n174: ```python\n175: # User: \"Search emails for project budget\"\n176: \n177: # Knowledge Assistant tool calls:\n178: email_config = load_email_config()\n179: with EmailConnector(email_config) as connector:\n180:     email_results = connector.search(\"project budget\", limit=5)\n181: \n182: # opencode response:\n183: display_email_results(email_results)\n184: ```\n185: \n186: ---\n187: \n188: ## 🗺️ Intent Mapping\n189: \n190: ### Intent Recognition Patterns\n191: \n192: | User Intent | Trigger Patterns | Mapped Tool | Priority |\n193: |-----------|-----------------|-------------|----------|\n194: | **build_knowledge_base** | \"build knowledge base\", \"create index\", \"构建知识库\" | `build_semantic_index()` | P0 |\n195: | **search_documents** | \"search for\", \"find documents\", \"搜索文档\" | `semantic_search()` | P0 |\n196: | **extract_keywords** | \"extract keywords\", \"关键词提取\" | `extract_keywords()` | P1 |\n197: | **generate_summary** | \"summarize\", \"生成摘要\" | `generate_summary()` | P1 |\n198: | **search_emails** | \"search emails\", \"搜索邮件\" | `EmailConnector.search()` | P1 |\n199: | **multi_source_search** | \"search all sources\", \"全局搜索\" | Multiple tools | P2 |\n200: \n201: ### Intent Recognition Flow\n202: \n203: ```\n204: User Input\n205:     ↓\n206: opencode NLU Engine\n207:     ↓\n208: Intent Classification\n209:     ├── \"build knowledge base\" → build_knowledge_base\n210:     ├── \"search for X\" → search_documents\n211:     ├── \"extract keywords\" → extract_knowledge\n212:     └── \"search emails\" → multi_source_search\n213:     ↓\n214: Parameter Extraction\n215:     ├── Extract: directory, query, filters\n216:     └── Validate: required parameters present\n217:     ↓\n218: Tool Invocation\n219:     └── Call appropriate Knowledge Assistant tool\n220:     ↓\n221: Result Processing\n222:     └── Return structured data to opencode\n223:     ↓\n224: User Presentation\n225:     └── opencode displays results\n226: ```\n227: \n228: ---\n229: \n230: ## 🔄 Workflow Descriptions\n231: \n232: ### Workflow 1: Build Knowledge Base\n233: \n234: **Trigger**: User wants to index a document collection.\n235: \n236: **Steps**:\n237: \n238: ```mermaid\n239: graph TD\n240:     A[User: Build KB from dir] --> B[opencode: Scan directory]\n241:     B --> C[opencode: Read documents]\n242:     C --> D[KA: build_semantic_index]\n243:     D --> E{Success?}\n244:     E -->|Yes| F[opencode: Report success]\n245:     E -->|No| G[opencode: Handle error]\n246:     G --> H[User: Fix issue or retry]\n247: ```\n248: \n249: **Detailed Flow**:\n250: \n251: 1. **User Request**\n252:    ```\n253:    User: \"Build knowledge base from ./notes\"\n254:    ```\n255: \n256: 2. **opencode Intent Recognition**\n257:    ```python\n258:    intent = recognize_intent(\"Build knowledge base from ./notes\")\n259:    # intent = {\n260:    #     'type': 'build_knowledge_base',\n261:    #     'parameters': {'directory': './notes'}\n262:    # }\n263:    ```\n264: \n265: 3. **opencode File Operations**\n266:    ```python\n267:    directory = intent['parameters']['directory']\n268:    documents = []\n269:    \n270:    for file_path in scan_directory(directory, recursive=True):\n271:        if is_supported_file(file_path):\n272:            content = read_file(file_path)\n273:            metadata = {\n274:                'path': file_path,\n275:                'title': extract_title(file_path),\n276:                'date': get_file_date(file_path)\n277:            }\n278:            documents.append({\n279:                'content': content,\n280:                'metadata': metadata\n281:            })\n282:    ```\n283: \n284: 4. **Knowledge Assistant Tool Call**\n285:    ```python\n286:    from scripts.tools.indexing import build_semantic_index\n287:    \n288:    result = build_semantic_index(\n289:        documents=documents,\n290:        index_path=\".ka-index\",\n291:        chunk_size=256,\n292:        chunk_overlap=50\n293:    )\n294:    ```\n295: \n296: 5. **opencode Response**\n297:    ```\n298:    ✓ Successfully built knowledge base!\n299:    \n300:    📊 Statistics:\n301:    - Documents indexed: 156\n302:    - Chunks created: 489\n303:    - Index size: 23.5 MB\n304:    - Build time: 12.3s\n305:    \n306:    💡 You can now search your documents using natural language!\n307:    ```\n308: \n309: ---\n310: \n311: ### Workflow 2: Semantic Search\n312: \n313: **Trigger**: User wants to find relevant documents.\n314: \n315: **Steps**:\n316: \n317: ```mermaid\n318: graph TD\n319:     A[User: Search for query] --> B[opencode: Recognize intent]\n320:     B --> C{Index exists?}\n321:     C -->|No| D[opencode: Prompt to build index]\n322:     C -->|Yes| E[KA: semantic_search]\n323:     E --> F[opencode: Read result docs]\n324:     F --> G[opencode: Display results]\n325: ```\n326: \n327: **Detailed Flow**:\n328: \n329: 1. **User Request**\n330:    ```\n331:    User: \"Find documents about Python async programming\"\n332:    ```\n333: \n334: 2. **opencode Intent Recognition**\n335:    ```python\n336:    intent = recognize_intent(\"Find documents about Python async programming\")\n337:    # intent = {\n338:    #     'type': 'search_documents',\n339:    #     'parameters': {\n340:    #         'query': 'Python async programming',\n341:    #         'top_k': 5\n342:    #     }\n343:    # }\n344:    ```\n345: \n346: 3. **opencode Validation**\n347:    ```python\n348:    if not index_exists(\".ka-index\"):\n349:        respond(\"I don't have a knowledge base yet. Would you like to build one?\")\n350:        return\n351:    ```\n352: \n353: 4. **Knowledge Assistant Tool Call**\n354:    ```python\n355:    from scripts.tools.search import semantic_search\n356:    \n357:    results = semantic_search(\n358:        query=\"Python async programming\",\n359:        index_path=\".ka-index\",\n360:        top_k=5\n361:    )\n362:    ```\n363: \n364: 5. **opencode Result Processing**\n365:    ```python\n366:    for i, result in enumerate(results, 1):\n367:        doc_path = result['metadata']['path']\n368:        content = read_file(doc_path)\n369:        \n370:        display_result(\n371:            rank=i,\n372:            title=result['metadata'].get('title', doc_path),\n373:            similarity=result['similarity'],\n374:            snippet=result['snippet'],\n375:            path=doc_path,\n376:            full_content=content  # User can request full content\n377:        )\n378:    ```\n379: \n380: 6. **opencode Response**\n381:    ```\n382:    Found 5 relevant documents for \"Python async programming\":\n383:    \n384:    ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n385:    \n386:    1. Python异步编程指南\n387:       📍 ./notes/python/async.md\n388:       📊 Similarity: 0.89\n389:       📝 Python async programming allows you to write concurrent code using the async/await syntax...\n390:    \n391:    2. 并发编程最佳实践\n392:       📍 ./notes/python/concurrency.md\n393:       📊 Similarity: 0.85\n394:       📝 When working with async programming in Python, consider the following best practices...\n395:    \n396:    ...\n397:    \n398:    💡 Say \"show full content of result 1\" to see the complete document.\n399:    ```\n400: \n401: ---\n402: \n403: ### Workflow 3: Knowledge Extraction\n404: \n405: **Trigger**: User wants to extract insights from a document.\n406: \n407: **Steps**:\n408: \n409: ```mermaid\n410: graph TD\n411:     A[User: Extract from doc] --> B[opencode: Read document]\n412:     B --> C[User: Keywords or Summary?]\n413:     C -->|Keywords| D[KA: extract_keywords]\n414:     C -->|Summary| E[KA: generate_summary]\n415:     C -->|Both| F[KA: Both tools]\n416:     D --> G[opencode: Display keywords]\n417:     E --> H[opencode: Display summary]\n418:     F --> I[opencode: Display both]\n419: ```\n420: \n421: **Detailed Flow**:\n422: \n423: 1. **User Request**\n424:    ```\n425:    User: \"Extract keywords and summarize ./notes/python.md\"\n426:    ```\n427: \n428: 2. **opencode Intent Recognition**\n429:    ```python\n430:    intent = recognize_intent(\"Extract keywords and summarize ./notes/python.md\")\n431:    # intent = {\n432:    #     'type': 'extract_knowledge',\n433:    #     'parameters': {\n434:    #         'document': './notes/python.md',\n435:    #         'tasks': ['keywords', 'summary']\n436:    #     }\n437:    # }\n438:    ```\n439: \n440: 3. **opencode File Operation**\n441:    ```python\n442:    content = read_file(\"./notes/python.md\")\n443:    ```\n444: \n445: 4. **Knowledge Assistant Tool Calls**\n446:    ```python\n447:    from scripts.tools.extraction import extract_keywords, generate_summary\n448:    \n449:    # Extract keywords\n450:    keywords = extract_keywords(\n451:        content=content,\n452:        method=\"textrank\",\n453:        top_n=10\n454:    )\n455:    \n456:    # Generate summary\n457:    summary = generate_summary(\n458:        content=content,\n459:        max_length=200\n460:    )\n461:    ```\n462: \n463: 5. **opencode Response**\n464:    ```\n465:    📄 Document: python.md\n466:    \n467:    ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n468:    \n469:    🔑 Top Keywords:\n470:    1. Python (score: 0.89)\n471:    2. 异步编程 (score: 0.85)\n472:    3. 并发 (score: 0.78)\n473:    4. async/await (score: 0.75)\n474:    5. 性能优化 (score: 0.72)\n475:    \n476:    ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n477:    \n478:    📝 Summary:\n479:    Python是一种广泛使用的编程语言，支持异步编程特性。通过async/await语法，可以编写高效的并发代码。异步编程适用于I/O密集型任务，能显著提升程序性能。\n480:    \n481:    Compression ratio: 15% (200 chars from 1300 original)\n482:    ```\n483: \n484: ---\n485: \n486: ### Workflow 4: Email Search\n487: \n488: **Trigger**: User wants to search emails.\n489: \n490: **Steps**:\n491: \n492: ```mermaid\n493: graph TD\n494:     A[User: Search emails] --> B[opencode: Check config]\n495:     B --> C{Config exists?}\n496:     C -->|No| D[opencode: Guide setup]\n497:     D --> E[User: Provide credentials]\n498:     C -->|Yes| F[KA: EmailConnector.connect]\n499:     E --> F\n500:     F --> G[KA: EmailConnector.search]\n501:     G --> H[opencode: Display emails]\n502: ```\n503: \n504: **Detailed Flow**:\n505: \n506: 1. **User Request**\n507:    ```\n508:    User: \"Search my emails for project budget\"\n509:    ```\n510: \n511: 2. **opencode Intent Recognition**\n512:    ```python\n513:    intent = recognize_intent(\"Search my emails for project budget\")\n514:    # intent = {\n515:    #     'type': 'search_emails',\n516:    #     'parameters': {\n517:    #         'query': 'project budget',\n518:    #         'limit': 5\n519:    #     }\n520:    # }\n521:    ```\n522: \n523: 3. **opencode Configuration Check**\n524:    ```python\n525:    email_config = load_email_config()\n526:    \n527:    if not email_config:\n528:        respond(\"\"\"\n529:        I need your email configuration to search emails. Please provide:\n530:        - IMAP server (e.g., imap.gmail.com)\n531:        - Email address\n532:        - Password or app password\n533:        \n534:        Your credentials will be stored securely.\n535:        \"\"\")\n536:        return\n537:    ```\n538: \n539: 4. **Knowledge Assistant Tool Call**\n540:    ```python\n541:    from scripts.connectors.email import EmailConnector, EmailConfig\n542:    \n543:    config = EmailConfig(\n544:        server=email_config['server'],\n545:        username=email_config['username'],\n546:        password=email_config['password']\n547:    )\n548:    \n549:    with EmailConnector(config) as connector:\n550:        results = connector.search(\n551:            query=\"project budget\",\n552:            limit=5,\n553:            folders=[\"INBOX\"]\n554:        )\n555:    ```\n556: \n557: 5. **opencode Response**\n558:    ```\n559:    Found 3 emails matching \"project budget\":\n560:    \n561:    ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n562:    \n563:    1. Budget Meeting Notes - Q1 Review\n564:       👤 From: boss@company.com\n565:       📅 Date: 2024-01-15 10:30\n566:       📁 Folder: INBOX\n567:       📝 Attached are the notes from today's budget meeting...\n568:    \n569:    2. Re: Budget Meeting Tomorrow\n570:       👤 From: colleague@company.com\n571:       📅 Date: 2024-01-14 16:45\n572:       📁 Folder: INBOX\n573:       📝 I'll prepare the budget meeting materials as discussed...\n574:    \n575:    ...\n576:    \n577:    💡 Say \"show email 1\" to see the full email content.\n578:    ```\n579: \n580: ---\n581: \n582: ## ⚙️ Configuration Guide\n583: \n584: ### Prerequisites\n585: \n586: **System Requirements**:\n587: - Python 3.8+\n588: - ~500MB RAM for indexing\n589: - ~200MB disk space for model\n590: \n591: **Dependencies**:\n592: ```bash\n593: pip install sentence-transformers faiss-cpu jieba scikit-learn\n594: ```\n595: \n596: **Optional** (for email search):\n597: ```bash\n598: pip install keyring  # For secure credential storage\n599: ```\n600: \n601: ---\n602: \n603: ### Initial Setup\n604: \n605: #### Step 1: Install Dependencies\n606: \n607: ```bash\n608: # Navigate to knowledge-assistant directory\n609: cd knowledge-assistant\n610: \n611: # Install required packages\n612: pip install -r requirements.txt\n613: ```\n614: \n615: #### Step 2: Verify Installation\n616: \n617: ```bash\n618: # Test semantic search\n619: python -c \"from scripts.tools.search import semantic_search; print('✓ Import successful')\"\n620: \n621: # Test email connector (optional)\n622: python -c \"from scripts.connectors.email import EmailConnector; print('✓ Email connector available')\"\n623: ```\n624: \n625: #### Step 3: Configure Email (Optional)\n626: \n627: **Option A: Using opencode Config**\n628: ```yaml\n629: # config.yaml\n630: email:\n631:   server: imap.gmail.com\n632:   username: your-email@gmail.com\n633:   password: your-app-password  # Use app password for Gmail\n634:   use_ssl: true\n635: ```\n636: \n637: **Option B: Interactive Setup**\n638: ```\n639: User: \"Search my emails\"\n640: opencode: \"I need your email configuration. What's your IMAP server?\"\n641: User: \"imap.gmail.com\"\n642: opencode: \"What's your email address?\"\n643: User: \"user@gmail.com\"\n644: opencode: \"Password or app password?\"\n645: User: \"xxxx xxxx xxxx xxxx\"\n646: opencode: \"✓ Email configured! I'll store this securely.\"\n647: ```\n648: \n649: ---\n650: \n651: ### First-Time Usage\n652: \n653: #### Build Your First Knowledge Base\n654: \n655: ```\n656: User: \"Build knowledge base from ./documents\"\n657: \n658: opencode:\n659:   [Scans directory...]\n660:   [Reads documents...]\n661:   [Building index...]\n662:   \n663:   ✓ Knowledge base created!\n664:   \n665:   📊 Statistics:\n666:   - Documents: 50\n667:   - Chunks: 150\n668:   - Build time: 5.2s\n669:   \n670:   💡 Try: \"Search for [topic]\" to find documents!\n671: ```\n672: \n673: #### Perform Your First Search\n674: \n675: ```\n676: User: \"Search for machine learning\"\n677: \n678: opencode:\n679:   [Searching...]\n680:   \n681:   Found 5 relevant documents:\n682:   \n683:   1. ML Guide for Beginners\n684:      Similarity: 0.92\n685:      Path: ./documents/ml-guide.md\n686:      Snippet: Machine learning is a subset of artificial intelligence...\n687:   \n688:   ...\n689: ```\n690: \n691: ---\n692: \n693: ## 🔒 Security Considerations\n694: \n695: ### Email Credentials\n696: \n697: **Best Practices**:\n698: - Use app-specific passwords (not main password)\n699: - Store credentials securely (keyring, environment variables)\n700: - Never log or display passwords\n701: - Support OAuth2 for production (future)\n702: \n703: **Implementation**:\n704: ```python\n705: # Good - secure credential handling\n706: import keyring\n707: \n708: def get_email_password(username: str) -> str:\n709:     \"\"\"Retrieve password from secure storage.\"\"\"\n710:     return keyring.get_password(\"knowledge-assistant\", username)\n711: \n712: def save_email_password(username: str, password: str):\n713:     \"\"\"Save password to secure storage.\"\"\"\n714:     keyring.set_password(\"knowledge-assistant\", username, password)\n715: \n716: # Bad - insecure\n717: password = \"my-password\"  # Don't hardcode!\n718: ```\n719: \n720: ### File Access\n721: \n722: **Best Practices**:\n723: - Respect file permissions\n724: - Don't read system files without explicit request\n725: - Validate paths to prevent directory traversal\n726: - Sanitize user input\n727: \n728: **Implementation**:\n729: ```python\n730: # Good - validate path\n731: def safe_read_file(path: str) -> str:\n732:     \"\"\"Read file with path validation.\"\"\"\n733:     # Resolve absolute path\n734:     abs_path = os.path.abspath(path)\n735:     \n736:     # Check if within allowed directories\n737:     if not is_allowed_directory(abs_path):\n738:         raise ValueError(f\"Access denied: {path}\")\n739:     \n740:     # Check file exists and is readable\n741:     if not os.path.isfile(abs_path):\n742:         raise FileNotFoundError(f\"File not found: {path}\")\n743:     \n744:     return read_file(abs_path)\n745: ```\n746: \n747: ---\n748: \n749: ## 📊 Performance Optimization\n750: \n751: ### Index Building\n752: \n753: **Tips**:\n754: - Use batch processing for large collections\n755: - Adjust chunk_size based on document types\n756: - Consider incremental updates for frequent changes\n757: \n758: **Performance Tuning**:\n759: ```python\n760: # Small documents (tweets, notes)\n761: build_semantic_index(docs, chunk_size=128, chunk_overlap=20)\n762: \n763: # Medium documents (articles, blogs)\n764: build_semantic_index(docs, chunk_size=256, chunk_overlap=50)  # Default\n765: \n766: # Large documents (reports, books)\n767: build_semantic_index(docs, chunk_size=512, chunk_overlap=100)\n768: ```\n769: \n770: ### Search Optimization\n771: \n772: **Tips**:\n773: - Use filters to narrow search space\n774: - Cache frequently used queries\n775: - Pre-warm the model on startup\n776: \n777: **Caching Example**:\n778: ```python\n779: from functools import lru_cache\n780: \n781: @lru_cache(maxsize=100)\n782: def cached_search(query: str, top_k: int):\n783:     \"\"\"Cache frequent searches.\"\"\"\n784:     return semantic_search(query, top_k=top_k)\n785: ```\n786: \n787: ---\n788: \n789: ## 🐛 Troubleshooting\n790: \n791: ### Common Issues\n792: \n793: #### 1. Model Download Fails\n794: \n795: **Symptom**: `RuntimeError: Failed to load model`\n796: \n797: **Solution**:\n798: ```bash\n799: # Manually download model\n800: python -c \"from sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer; SentenceTransformer('BAAI/bge-small-zh-v1.5')\"\n801: ```\n802: \n803: #### 2. Index Not Found\n804: \n805: **Symptom**: `FileNotFoundError: Index not found`\n806: \n807: **Solution**:\n808: ```\n809: User: \"Search for Python\"\n810: opencode: \"I don't have a knowledge base yet. Build one first with:\n811:           'Build knowledge base from [directory]'\"\n812: ```\n813: \n814: #### 3. Email Connection Fails\n815: \n816: **Symptom**: `imaplib.IMAP4.error: Authentication failed`\n817: \n818: **Solution**:\n819: ```\n820: User: \"Search emails\"\n821: opencode: \"Email connection failed. Check:\n822:           - IMAP server is correct\n823:           - Using app password (not regular password)\n824:           - IMAP is enabled in email settings\n825:           \n826:           Would you like to reconfigure?\"\n827: ```\n828: \n829: ---\n830: \n831: ## 🔮 Future Roadmap\n832: \n833: ### v1.2 (Next Release)\n834: \n835: - **Incremental Indexing**: Update without rebuild\n836: - **PDF Support**: Extract text from PDFs\n837: - **Code Search**: Specialized code indexing\n838: - **Result Caching**: Faster repeated searches\n839: \n840: ### v1.3 (Planned)\n841: \n842: - **RAG Integration**: Retrieval-augmented generation\n843: - **Multi-Language**: Support English + Chinese\n844: - **Cloud Sync**: Share knowledge bases\n845: - **API Endpoint**: RESTful API access\n846: \n847: ### v2.0 (Vision)\n848: \n849: - **Knowledge Graph**: Entity relationships\n850: - **Auto-Categorization**: Smart tagging\n851: - **Collaborative KB**: Team knowledge bases\n852: - **Voice Interface**: Voice commands\n853: \n854: ---\n855: \n856: ## 📚 References\n857: \n858: ### Documentation\n859: \n860: - [SKILL.md](./skills/knowledge-assistant/SKILL.md) - Skill definition\n861: - [Technical Design](./docs/technical-design-v1.1.md) - Architecture details\n862: - [Email Connector Guide](./docs/email-connector-guide.md) - Email setup\n863: \n864: ### Examples\n865: \n866: - [Usage Examples](./docs/usage-examples.md) - Complete examples\n867: - [Integration Tests](./tests/integration/) - Test cases\n868: \n869: ---\n870: \n871: ## 📝 Version History\n872: \n873: | Version | Date | Changes |\n874: |---------|------|---------|\n875: | v1.1 | 2026-03-07 | Initial agent configuration |\n876: | v1.0 | 2026-02-15 | Project conception |\n877: \n878: ---\n879: \n880: **Maintained by**: Integration Team  \n881: **Contact**: Create an issue at GitHub repository  \n882: **License**: MIT\n\n(End of file - total 882 lines)\n</content>","title":"AGENT.md","metadata":{"preview":"# Knowledge Assistant Agent Configuration\n\n> 🤖 Agent configuration for opencode integration\n\n**Version**: v1.1  \n**Last Updated**: 2026-03-07  \n**Author**: Integration Team  \n**Status**: Production Ready\n\n---\n\n## 📖 Overview\n\n**Knowledge Assistant Agent** is a specialized agent that provides intelligent knowledge management capabilities to opencode. It serves as a bridge between user intents and the Knowledge Assistant tool library.\n\n### Agent Identity\n\n- **Name**: Knowledge Assistant\n- **Type**: Specialized Tool Agent\n- **Role**: Knowledge Management Specialist","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1772871970894,"end":1772871970897}}}}
